"use strict";(self.webpackChunkhackmajoris_blog=self.webpackChunkhackmajoris_blog||[]).push([[450],{6029:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/2023/03/11/dispari\u021bia-b\u0103ncii","metadata":{"permalink":"/2023/03/11/dispari\u021bia-b\u0103ncii","source":"@site/blog/2023-03-11-dispari\u021bia-b\u0103ncii.md","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Dispari\u021bia b\u0103ncii Silicon Valley","description":"Sursa tradusa. Sursa originala","date":"2023-03-11T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"March 11, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":15.05,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Alexandru Ilies"}],"frontMatter":{"layout":"post","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Dispari\u021bia b\u0103ncii Silicon Valley","author":"Alexandru Ilies"},"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Amazon RDS Start-Stop Scheduler with CDK and TypeScript","permalink":"/2023/01/23/rds-start-stop-scheduler"}},"content":"Sursa tradusa. Sursa [originala](https://www.netinterest.co/p/the-demise-of-silicon-valley-bank)\\n\\nUn articol ce merit\u0103 tradus \u0219i r\u0103sp\xe2ndit \xeen c\xe2t mai multe limbi, pentru a \xeen\u021belege cum func\u021bioneaz\u0103 sistemul bancar.\\n\\n\\n# \\"Colapsul rapid al celei de-a 16-a celei mai mari b\u0103nci din America\\"\\n\\n## C\xe2nd nu lucrezi, ce faci pentru a reduce stresul?\\"\\n\\nAcesta a fost ultima \xeentrebare la care Greg Becker, CEO al Silicon Valley Bank, a r\u0103spuns la o conferin\u021b\u0103 de investitori \xeen aceast\u0103 s\u0103pt\u0103m\xe2n\u0103.\\n\\"Ciclismu, este sfatul meu\\", a r\u0103spuns el. \\"Locuind \xeen nordul Californiei \u0219i fiind pe peninsul\u0103. Cred c\u0103 este cea mai bun\u0103 zon\u0103 cu pist\u0103 de biciclete din\\nlume, punct.\\"\\nLa trei zile dup\u0103 aceasta, banca lui Becker se afl\u0103 \xeen administrare judiciar\u0103.\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\nAm discutat anterior despre riscul de dob\xe2nd\u0103 care p\xe2nde\u0219te bilan\u021burile b\u0103ncilor \u0219i despre modul \xeen care industria \xeel gestioneaz\u0103. \xcen timpul\\npandemiei, b\u0103ncile au primit volume record de noi depozite. \xcentre sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2019 \u0219i primul trimestru al anului 2022, depozitele la b\u0103ncile\\namericane au crescut cu 5,40 trilioane de dolari. Cu cererea de \xeemprumut slab\u0103, doar aproximativ 15% din acest volum a fost canalizat c\u0103tre\\n\xeemprumuturi; restul a fost investit \xeen portofolii de titluri sau p\u0103strat sub form\u0103 de numerar. Portofoliile de titluri s-au extins la 6,26 trilioane\\nde dolari, \xeen cre\u0219tere de la 3,98 trilioane de dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2019, iar balan\u021bele de numerar au crescut la 3,38 trilioane de dolari fa\u021b\u0103\\nde 1,67 trilioane de dolari.\\n\\nC\xe2nd b\u0103ncile achizi\u021bioneaz\u0103 titluri de valoare, sunt obligate s\u0103 decid\u0103 \xeenainte dac\u0103 inten\u021bioneaz\u0103 s\u0103 le de\u021bin\u0103 p\xe2n\u0103 la scaden\u021b\u0103. Decizia dicteaz\u0103\\ndac\u0103 titlurile sunt desemnate ca active \\"\u021binute p\xe2n\u0103 la scaden\u021b\u0103\\" (HTM) sau ca active \\"disponibile pentru v\xe2nzare\\" (AFS). Activele HTM nu sunt marcate\\nla pia\u021b\u0103: b\u0103ncile pot privi f\u0103r\u0103 grij\u0103 cum obliga\u021biunile pierd valoare; acestea r\u0103m\xe2n lipite de bilan\u021b la costul amortizat indiferent. \xcen schimb,\\nactivele AFS sunt marcate la pia\u021b\u0103 - o desemnare mai pur\u0103, dar care injecteaz\u0103 un element de volatilitate \xeen baza de capital a unei b\u0103nci. Pentru\\nb\u0103ncile mai mici, reglementatorii trec cu vederea aceast\u0103 volatilitate, dar pentru b\u0103ncile cu active de peste 700 miliarde de dolari, aceast\u0103\\nvolatilitate afecteaz\u0103 direct capitalul reglementar.\\n\\nDar apoi a\u0219tept\u0103rile privind rata dob\xe2nzii au \xeenceput s\u0103 se schimbe \u0219i pre\u021burile obliga\u021biunilor au \xeenceput s\u0103 scad\u0103. Dup\u0103 ce au stat pe c\xe2\u0219tigurile\\nne\xeenregistrate pe pia\u021ba de valori ale portofoliilor lor de valori mobiliare, b\u0103ncile au \xeenceput s\u0103 vad\u0103 apari\u021bia pierderilor. C\xe2\u0219tigurile\\nne\xeenregistrate de 39 miliarde de dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2020 pentru portofoliile AFS ale b\u0103ncilor au trecut la pierderi ne\xeenregistrate de 31\\nmiliarde de dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2021.\\n\\nPentru a opri scurgerea de bani, multe b\u0103nci au reclasificat valorile mobiliare AFS ca fiind HTM. Acest lucru \xeenseamn\u0103 recunoa\u0219terea pierderilor \xeen\\navans, dar schimbarea ar proteja balan\u021bele de alte pierderi pe m\u0103sur\u0103 ce pre\u021burile obliga\u021biunilor continuau s\u0103 scad\u0103. Cea mai mare banc\u0103, JPMorgan, a\\ntransferat 342 miliarde de dolari din valori mobiliare AFS \xeen valori mobiliare HTM, reduc\xe2nd ponderea AFS la 30%. Altele au urmat: \xcen \xeentreaga\\nindustrie, ponderea valorilor mobiliare de\u021binute ca AFS a sc\u0103zut de la trei sferturi la pu\u021bin peste jum\u0103tate la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2022.\\n\\nDiferite b\u0103nci au adoptat diferite strategii. JPMorgan a re\u021binut o mul\u021bime de numerar \u0219i a ales s\u0103 gestioneze agresiv portofoliul AFS. \\"Vindem valori\\nmobiliare scumpe \u0219i cump\u0103r\u0103m cele ieftine\\", a spus CEO-ul Jamie Dimon \xeen apelul s\u0103u de c\xe2\u0219tiguri al celui de-al treilea trimestru. Fifth Third a decis\\ns\u0103 a\u0219tepte \xeenainte de a-\u0219i investi depozitele excedentare \xeen valori mobiliare. \\"Ne permitem s\u0103 fim r\u0103bd\u0103tori\\", a spus CFO-ul s\u0103u \xeentr-un apel de\\nc\xe2\u0219tiguri \xeen ianuarie 2021. Fifth Third a f\u0103cut probabil mutarea prea devreme \xeen 2022, dar totu\u0219i a reu\u0219it s\u0103 ob\u021bin\u0103 randamente pu\u021bin mai bune dec\xe2t\\nb\u0103ncile care au investit pe pia\u021b\u0103 mai devreme.\\n\\nUnele b\u0103nci au gre\u0219it complet. First Republic este una dintre acestea despre care am discutat \xeen octombrie. O alt\u0103 banc\u0103 care a gre\u0219it, evident, este\\nSilicon Valley Bank.\\n\\n## O privire \xeen bilan\u021bul Silicon Valley\\n\\nSilicon Valley Bank a fost \xeenfiin\u021bat\u0103 \xeen 1983 pentru a servi ecosistemul tehnologic \xeen plin\u0103 dezvoltare din Valea Sillicon. Reglement\u0103rile revizuite\\nau u\u0219urat procesul de ob\u021binere a unei licen\u021be bancare, iar Silicon Valley Bank a devenit una dintre cele 72 de b\u0103nci noi lansate \xeen California \xeen acel\\nan. A crescut \xeencet, supravie\u021buind unui colaps imobiliar care a dus la o pierdere semnificativ\u0103 \xeen 1992, \xeenainte de a se confrunta cu boom-ul \u0219i\\npr\u0103bu\u0219irea tehnologic\u0103 c\xe2\u021biva ani mai t\xe2rziu.\\n\\nSilicon Valley Bank ofer\u0103 companiilor tech o gam\u0103 larg\u0103 de produse: servicii de depozit, \xeemprumuturi, produse de investi\u021bii, managementul cash-ului,\\nfinan\u021be comerciale \u0219i multe altele. Deoarece companiile mai tinere au tendin\u021ba de a avea mai multe disponibilit\u0103\u021bi de numerar dec\xe2t datorii,\\nmajoritatea banilor b\u0103ncii sunt ob\u021binu\u021bi \xeen mod tradi\u021bional din partea activit\u0103\u021bii de depozit.\\n\\nImpulsionat\u0103 de boom-ul finan\u021b\u0103rii de capital de risc, mul\u021bi dintre clien\u021bii Silicon Valley au avut un surplus de bani \xeen 2020 \u0219i 2021. \xcentre\\nsf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2019 \u0219i primul trimestru al anului 2022, balan\u021ba depozitelor b\u0103ncii s-a triplat, ajung\xe2nd la 198 de miliarde de dolari (inclusiv o\\nmic\u0103 achizi\u021bie a Boston Private Financial Holdings). Acest lucru se compar\u0103 cu o cre\u0219tere a depozitelor din industrie de \u201edoar\u201d 37% \xeen perioada\\nrespectiv\u0103. Aproximativ dou\u0103 treimi din depozitele erau depozite de cerere neremunerate \u0219i restul ofereau o rat\u0103 mic\u0103 de dob\xe2nd\u0103. \xcen total, la\\nsf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2022, costul depozitelor Silicon Valley era de 1,17% (fa\u021b\u0103 de 0,04% la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2021).\\n\\nBanca a investit majoritatea acestor depozite \xeen valori mobiliare. A adoptat o strategie \xeen dou\u0103 etape: s\u0103-\u0219i protejeze o parte din lichidit\u0103\u021bi \xeen\\nvalori mobiliare disponibile pentru v\xe2nzare cu durat\u0103 mai scurt\u0103, \xeen timp ce c\u0103uta randamentul cu o carte cu durat\u0103 mai lung\u0103 de\u021binut\u0103 p\xe2n\u0103 la\\nscaden\u021b\u0103. Pe baza costului, cartea AFS cu durat\u0103 mai scurt\u0103 a crescut de la 13,9 miliarde de dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2019 la 27,3 miliarde de\\ndolari la v\xe2rf \xeen primul trimestru al anului 2022; cartea HTM cu durat\u0103 mai lung\u0103 a crescut mult mai mult: de la 13,8 miliarde de dolari la 98,7\\nmiliarde de dolari. Parte din cre\u0219tere reflect\u0103 transferul de 8,8 miliarde de dolari de valori mobiliare de la AFS la HTM, dar majoritatea reflect\u0103\\nachizi\u021bii pe pia\u021b\u0103.\\n\\n\\"Pe baza mediului actual, am plasa probabil banii \xeen plaj\u0103 de 1,65%, 1,75%\\", a spus CFO-ul b\u0103ncii la \xeenceputul anului 2022, referindu-se la\\nrandamentele pe care dorea s\u0103 le ob\u021bin\u0103. \\"Majoritatea fiind garan\u021bii ipotecare ale agen\u021biilor, garan\u021bii colaterale ipotecare, lucruri de genul\\nacesta.\\"\\n\\n![](https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2f1cc305-bb27-4a12-99f5-5f6a0c000eb4_733x478.png)\\n\\nNot\u0103: Toate datele sunt \xeen milioane de dolari americani, cumulate \xeencep\xe2nd cu decembrie 2019; evalu\u0103rile valorilor titlurilor sunt exprimate la costul\\namortizat.\\n\\nProblema este c\u0103 atunci c\xe2nd ratele au \xeenceput s\u0103 creasc\u0103, activele ipotecare au fost lovite puternic. Durata portofoliului HTM al Silicon Valley a\\najuns la 6,2 ani, la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2022, iar pierderile ne\xeenregistrate au crescut de la zero \xeen iunie 2021, la 16 miliarde de dolari \xeen septembrie\\n\\n2022. Aceasta reprezint\u0103 o sc\u0103dere de 17% pe pia\u021ba marcat\u0103. Cartea mai mic\u0103 AFS a fost de asemenea afectat\u0103, dar nu la fel de r\u0103u. Pierderile marcate\\n      la valoarea de pia\u021b\u0103 au ajuns la 9% la sf\xe2r\u0219itul lunii septembrie.\\n\\nPierderile au fost at\xe2t de mari \xeenc\xe2t, din punct de vedere al valorii de pia\u021b\u0103, Silicon Valley Bank era tehnic insolvent la sf\xe2r\u0219itul lunii\\nseptembrie. Pierderile marcate la valoarea de pia\u021b\u0103 de 15,9 miliarde de dolari ale HTM au absorbit complet cele 11,8 miliarde de dolari din capitalul\\ncomun tangibil care a sus\u021binut bilan\u021bul b\u0103ncii.\\n\\nRe\u021bine\u021bi \xeens\u0103 c\u0103 aceste pierderi nu trebuie \xeenregistrate \xeen c\u0103r\u021bile b\u0103ncii, a\u0219a c\u0103 CEO-ul Silicon Valley ar putea s\u0103 ia bicicleta pentru o plimbare\\nf\u0103r\u0103 griji. De\u0219i nu este ideal pentru marja sa - \xeen pia\u021b\u0103 erau disponibile randamente mult mai mari dec\xe2t cele 1,65%, 1,75% pe care banca le-a\\nurm\u0103rit - situa\u021bia nu a fost fatal\u0103. \u201eVestea bun\u0103 este c\u0103 portofoliul de titluri valoreaz\u0103 constant. Deci vedem aproximativ 3 miliarde de dolari pe\\ntrimestru \u201d, a spus CFO-ul grupului \xeen apelul s\u0103u de c\xe2\u0219tiguri din al treilea trimestru. Va dura mult timp, dar se a\u0219tepta ca pierderile s\u0103 se desfac\u0103\\npe m\u0103sur\u0103 ce obliga\u021biunile sunt r\u0103scump\u0103rate.\\n\\nCeea ce nici CEO-ul, nici CFO-ul nu au anticipat, \xeens\u0103, a fost c\u0103 depozitele ar putea sc\u0103dea mai rapid. Ceea ce este ciudat, deoarece au v\u0103zut c\u0103\\ndepozitele s-au redus \xeen urm\u0103 cu 20 de ani, \xeen urma pr\u0103bu\u0219irii dotcom, c\xe2nd depozitele b\u0103ncii au sc\u0103zut de la 4,5 miliarde de dolari la 3,4 miliarde\\nde dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2001, pe m\u0103sur\u0103 ce clien\u021bii au utilizat rezervele lor de numerar.\\n\\nDirectorul de Risc poate c\u0103 a observat c\xe2teva semne de \xeengrijorare, dar nu a stat s\u0103 afle mai multe. Ea \u0219i-a p\u0103r\u0103sit pozi\u021bia \xeen aprilie 2022 (dup\u0103 ce\\na v\xe2ndut unele ac\u021biuni \xeen decembrie) \u0219i nu a fost \xeenlocuit\u0103 p\xe2n\u0103 \xeen ianuarie 2023.\\n\\nDe data aceasta, depozitele au sc\u0103zut de la 198 de miliarde de dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul lunii martie 2022 la 173 de miliarde de dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul lui\\ndecembrie (\u0219i la 165 de miliarde de dolari la sf\xe2r\u0219itul lunii februarie 2023). O parte din declin reflect\u0103 o contrac\u021bie la nivelul \xeentregului sistem.\\n\xcenainte de 2022, \xeen ultimii cincizeci de ani, \xeen SUA s-au \xeenregistrat doar zece trimestre de ie\u0219iri de depozite; acum am v\u0103zut patru trimestre de\\nie\u0219iri. Dar factorii care au dus la cre\u0219terea cotei de pia\u021b\u0103 a Silicon Valley Bank \xeen timpul cre\u0219terii sunt instrumentali \xeen pierderea cotei de pia\u021b\u0103\\npe parcursul declinului.\\n\\nPentru a-\u0219i rea\u0219eza bilan\u021bul pentru a se adapta ie\u0219irilor de depozite \u0219i a cre\u0219te flexibilitatea, Silicon Valley a v\xe2ndut s\u0103pt\u0103m\xe2na aceasta 21 de\\nmiliarde de dolari \xeen valori mobiliare disponibile pentru v\xe2nzare pentru a ob\u021bine lichidit\u0103\u021bi. Deoarece pierderea (1,8 miliarde de dolari dup\u0103\\nimpozitare) va fi absorbit\u0103 \xeen pozi\u021bia sa de capital reglementar, banca a trebuit s\u0103-\u0219i m\u0103reasc\u0103 capitalul odat\u0103 cu restructurarea.\\n\\nDin pacate, majorarea capitalului nu a fost realizat\u0103 niciodat\u0103. Banca a ales s\u0103 anun\u021be restructurarea bilan\u021bului \xeen aceea\u0219i zi \xeen care Silvergate\\nCapital a anun\u021bat c\u0103 intr\u0103 \xeen lichidare voluntar\u0103. Am discutat despre Silvergate s\u0103pt\u0103m\xe2na trecut\u0103. Modelele de afaceri sunt destul de diferite, dar\\nprovoc\u0103rile privind trezoreria nu sunt. Ambele b\u0103nci au avut probleme \xeen a-\u0219i limita pierderile de obliga\u021biuni \xeentr-un moment \xeen care pierdeau\\ndepozite. Temerile clien\u021bilor au transformat scurgerea lent\u0103 de depozite a Silicon Valley Bank \xeentr-un val.\\n\\n![](https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa5164a37-e480-47a0-8870-20390a2dc885_733x478.png)\\n\\n## Infarct miocardic \xeen trezorerie\\n\\n\xcen era digital\u0103, nu am avut niciodat\u0103 o criz\u0103 bancar\u0103. Northern Rock din Marea Britanie \xeen 2007 a fost anterior perioadei de banking mobil; este\\namintit prin imagini cu deponen\u021bi care a\u0219teptau r\xe2ndul (cu r\u0103bdare) \xeen afara filialelor sale de suburbi. \xcen 2019, un zvon fals pe WhatsApp a declan\u0219at\\no mic\u0103 criz\u0103 la Metro Bank, de asemenea \xeen Marea Britanie, dar a fost localizat\u0103 \u0219i rezolvat\u0103 rapid. Credit Suisse a pierdut 37% din depozitele sale\\n\xeentr-un singur trimestru la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului trecut, pe m\u0103sur\u0103 ce se intensificau preocup\u0103rile cu privire la pozi\u021bia sa financiar\u0103, cu toate acestea,\\ncel pu\u021bin interna\u021bional, retragerile de \xeenalt\u0103 valoare ar fi trebuit s\u0103 fie f\u0103cute prin telefon, nu prin intermediul unei aplica\u021bii.\\n\\nProblema, desigur, este c\u0103 procesarea unei retrageri online este mai rapid\u0103 \u0219i mai eficient\u0103 dec\xe2t prin intermediul unei filiale. \u0218i, de\u0219i imaginea\\nunei crize poate fi diferit\u0103, nu este mai pu\u021bin vizibil\u0103. Ieri, Twitter a fost inundat cu pove\u0219ti despre firmele de capital de risc care au instruit\\ncompaniile din portofoliu s\u0103-\u0219i mute fondurile din Silicon Valley Bank. Oamenii au postat capturi de ecran ale site-ului Silicon Valley Bank care se\\nlupta s\u0103 fac\u0103 fa\u021b\u0103 cererii utilizatorilor. Greg Becker, CEO-ul b\u0103ncii, a fost nevoit s\u0103 organizeze o \xeent\xe2lnire cu cei mai importan\u021bi capitali\u0219ti de\\nrisc. \\"A\u0219 ruga pe toat\u0103 lumea s\u0103 r\u0103m\xe2n\u0103 calm\u0103 \u0219i s\u0103 ne sus\u021bin\u0103 la fel cum v-am sus\u021binut \xeen timpurile dificile\\", a spus el.\\n\\n![](https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F193058b9-4d70-4877-88cc-fd7b46e3ff3f_1144x2479.jpeg)\\n\\n[Editare: Conform unei ordonan\u021be emise de regulatorul bancar din California, Departamentul de Protec\u021bie \u0219i Inovare Financiar\u0103, clien\u021bii au ini\u021biat retrageri de 42 de miliarde de dolari din depozitele b\u0103ncii pe 9 martie 2023, echivalentul a un sfert din totalul depozitelor sale.]\\n\\nProblema la Silicon Valley Bank este amplificat\u0103 de baza sa relativ concentrat\u0103 de clien\u021bi. \xcen ni\u0219a sa, to\u021bi clien\u021bii s\u0103i se cunosc \xeentre ei. \u0218i\\nSilicon Valley Bank nu are at\xe2t de mul\u021bi clien\u021bi. La sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2022, avea 37.466 de clien\u021bi de depozite, fiecare av\xe2nd \xeen cont sume de peste\\n250.000 de dolari. Excelent pentru recomand\u0103ri c\xe2nd afacerea prosper\u0103, aceast\u0103 concentrare poate amplifica un cerc vicios c\xe2nd condi\u021biile se\\ninverseaz\u0103.\\n\\n\xcentr-adev\u0103r, pragul de 250.000 de dolari este foarte relevant. Acesta reprezint\u0103 limita pentru asigurarea depozitelor. \xcen total, clien\u021bii cu solduri\\nmai mari dec\xe2t aceasta reprezint\u0103 157 miliarde de dolari din baza de depozite a Silicon Valley Bank, av\xe2nd \xeen medie 4,2 milioane de dolari \xeen cont\\nfiecare. Banca mai are \xeenc\u0103 106.420 de clien\u021bi ale c\u0103ror conturi sunt complet asigurate, dar ace\u0219tia controleaz\u0103 doar 4,8 miliarde de dolari din\\ndepozite. \xcen compara\u021bie cu b\u0103ncile mai orientate c\u0103tre consumatori, baza de depozite a Silicon Valley Bank se \xeendreapt\u0103 foarte mult spre depozitele\\nneasigurate. Din totalul s\u0103u de 173 de miliarde de dolari de depozite la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2022, 152 de miliarde de dolari sunt neasigurate.\\n\\nDeci, cum ar fi putut banca s\u0103 satisfac\u0103 cererile de retragere ale clien\u021bilor?\\n\\nUn lucru pe care nu l-ar fi putut face ar fi s\u0103 acceseze portofoliul s\u0103u de titluri de\u021binute p\xe2n\u0103 la maturitate. V\xe2nzarea unui singur bond ar declan\u0219a\\nevaluarea \xeentregului portofoliu pe pia\u021b\u0103, ceea ce banca nu ar fi avut capitalul necesar pentru a-l absorbi.\\n\\nAr fi putut s\u0103 \xeei ademeneasc\u0103 pe depun\u0103tori \xeenapoi cu rate mai mari (a\u0219a cum a \xeencercat Credit Suisse). \xcen special, Silicon Valley Bank supravegheaz\u0103\\n161 miliarde de dolari de fonduri ale clien\u021bilor \xeen afara bilan\u021bului (la sf\xe2r\u0219itul lunii februarie), pe care le-ar fi putut atrage \xeenapoi pe bilan\u021bul\\ns\u0103u. Dar banca ofer\u0103 deja 1,17% dob\xe2nd\u0103 la depozite, ceea ce este aproape de dou\u0103 ori mai mare dec\xe2t media de 0,65% a marilor b\u0103nci din SUA. \u0218i...\\nbine... peste 250.000 de dolari \u0219i nu e\u0219ti asigurat.\\n\\nAr fi putut s\u0103 \xeemprumute fonduri. Anul trecut, Silicon Valley Bank a apelat la Federal Home Loan Bank of San Francisco pentru 15 miliarde de dolari \u0219i\\navea capacitatea de a \xeemprumuta mai mult. Am discutat despre Federal Home Loan Bank of San Francisco aici s\u0103pt\u0103m\xe2na trecut\u0103 \xeen contextul lui\\nSilvergate. Ei sunt cei care au oprit liniile lor de finan\u021bare c\u0103tre Silvergate, duc\xe2ndu-l \xeen lichidare. La sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului, Silicon Valley Bank era\\ndeja cel mai mare \xeemprumut\u0103tor al lor, reprezent\xe2nd 17% din avansuri. Pentru a bloca acel \xeemprumut, Silicon Valley Bank a trebuit s\u0103 garanteze 19\\nmiliarde de dolari \xeen active. Problema este c\u0103 nu este ieftin. Banca a pl\u0103tit 4,17% pe totalul \xeemprumuturilor pe termen scurt la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului\\n2022, din care finan\u021barea Federal Home Loan Bank este cea mai mare parte. \xcen raport cu un randament de 1,79% pe portofoliul de titluri de\u021binute p\xe2n\u0103\\nla maturitate, nu este o afacere prea atractiv\u0103.\\n\\nToat\u0103 aceast\u0103 situa\u021bie a devenit acum nul\u0103. Criza a \xeensemnat c\u0103 ridicarea de capital pentru acoperirea pierderilor din portofoliul AFS a fost anulat\u0103,\\nl\u0103s\xe2nd Silicon Valley Bank subcapitalizat\u0103. Mai devreme ast\u0103zi, banca a fost \xeenchis\u0103 de c\u0103tre Departamentul pentru Protec\u021bia \u0219i Inovarea Financiar\u0103\\ndin California (care a avut o s\u0103pt\u0103m\xe2n\u0103 aglomerat\u0103, cu Silvergate de asemenea), care a invocat lipsa de lichiditate \u0219i\\ninsolven\u021ba. [Edit: Departamentul DFPI al Californiei a dezv\u0103luit c\u0103, la \xeenchiderea activit\u0103\u021bii la 9 martie, Silicon Valley Bank avea un sold negativ de numerar de aproximativ 958 de milioane de dolari \u0219i c\u0103, \xeen ciuda \xeencerc\u0103rilor de a transfera garan\u021bii din diferite surse, nu a \xeendeplinit \\"scrisoarea de numerar\\" cu Federal Reserve.]\\n\\nCorpora\u021bia Federal\u0103 de Asigurare a Depozitelor (FDIC) a fost numit\u0103 curator. Toate depozitele asigurate au fost transferate la o banc\u0103 nou creat\u0103,\\nBanca Na\u021bional\u0103 de Asigurare a Depozitelor din Santa Clara (DINB). Depozitorii neasigura\u021bi, \xeen schimb, sunt l\u0103sa\u021bi \xeen aer. Ace\u0219tia vor primi un \\"\\ndividend \xeen avans\\" s\u0103pt\u0103m\xe2na viitoare, iar pl\u0103\u021bile ulterioare de dividende depind de v\xe2nzarea activelor Silicon Valley Bank de c\u0103tre FDIC.\\n\\n\xcen fericire, planul de rezolu\u021bie al Silicon Valley Bank este \xeenc\u0103 proasp\u0103t. Banca a devenit suficient de mare \xeen 2021, \xeenc\xe2t reglementatorii au cerut\\ns\u0103 elaboreze un \\"testament viu\\" la fiecare trei ani. Silicon Valley Bank \u0219i-a prezentat primul astfel de document \xeen decembrie.\\n\\n## Concluzie\\n\\nAceast\u0103 situa\u021bie va arunca probabil o umbr\u0103 lung\u0103 asupra industriei \xeen general. Au trecut 868 de zile de la ultima falimentare a unei b\u0103nci din SUA,\\naproape de cel mai lung interval \xeenregistrat. \xcentre timp, consumatorii s-au obi\u0219nuit cu riscul, ceea ce se reflect\u0103 \xeen cre\u0219terea depozitelor\\nneasigurate, inclusiv \xeen portofelele digitale.\\n\\nUna dintre caracteristicile crizelor bancare este c\u0103 acestea rareori se repet\u0103 consecutiv. Acest lucru conteaz\u0103 deoarece factorii de decizie au\\ntendin\u021ba de a elabora reguli bazate pe ultima criz\u0103. Testele de stres din SUA includ diverse scenarii de credite neperformante, dar pu\u021bine privind\\n\u0219ocurile de dob\xe2nd\u0103. Scenariul sever negativ pentru randamentele la Trezorerie pe 10 ani este de 0,8-1,5%; scenariul de baz\u0103, care reflect\u0103 o\\nrecesiune mai u\u0219oar\u0103, include randamente de 3,2-3,9%.\\n\\n\xcen Europa, riscul de dob\xe2nd\u0103 este supravegheat de reglementatori prin Ratios de Acoperire a Lichidit\u0103\u021bii (LCR). Acestea cer b\u0103ncilor s\u0103 de\u021bin\u0103\\nsuficiente active lichide de \xeenalt\u0103 calitate (HQLA), cum ar fi datoria guvernamental\u0103 pe termen scurt, care pot fi v\xe2ndute pentru a finan\u021ba b\u0103ncile\\n\xeentr-un scenariu de stres de 30 de zile elaborat de reglementatori. B\u0103ncile trebuie s\u0103 de\u021bin\u0103 HQLA echivalent cu cel pu\u021bin 100% din fluxurile de\\nnumerar proiectate \xeen timpul scenariului de stres.\\n\\nCredit Suisse a rezistat cre\u0219terii depozitelor nea\u0219igurate cu un LCR mediu de 144% (de\u0219i a sc\u0103zut de la 192% la sf\xe2r\u0219itul celui de-al treilea\\ntrimestru). Silicon Valley Bank nu a fost niciodat\u0103 supus cerin\u021belor de LCR ale Federal Reserve - chiar \u0219i ca a 16-a cea mai mare banc\u0103 din America, a\\nfost considerat\u0103 prea mic\u0103. Este o ru\u0219ine. Reglementarea nu este o panaceu deoarece b\u0103ncile sunt pl\u0103tite s\u0103 ia riscuri. Cu toate acestea, un cadru\\nreglementar care s\u0103 se potriveasc\u0103 riscurilor zilei pare potrivit \u0219i este unul pentru care factorii de decizie americani pot fi acum nevoi\u021bi s\u0103 se\\ngr\u0103beasc\u0103.\\n\\npl\u0103tit, v\u0103 rug\u0103m s\u0103 v\u0103 \xeenscrie\u021bi pentru con\u021binut s\u0103pt\u0103m\xe2nal despre sectorul financiar \u0219i o arhiv\u0103 voluminoas\u0103 de peste 100 de numere anterioare."},{"id":"/2023/01/23/rds-start-stop-scheduler","metadata":{"permalink":"/2023/01/23/rds-start-stop-scheduler","source":"@site/blog/2023-01-23-rds-start-stop-scheduler.md","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Amazon RDS Start-Stop Scheduler with CDK and TypeScript","description":"Creating a schedule for your Amazon RDS instances and clusters can help you save money on running costs, and also ensure that your database is only running when it\'s needed.","date":"2023-01-23T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 23, 2023","tags":[],"readingTime":4.265,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Alexandru Ilies"}],"frontMatter":{"layout":"post","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Amazon RDS Start-Stop Scheduler with CDK and TypeScript","author":"Alexandru Ilies"},"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Dispari\u021bia b\u0103ncii Silicon Valley","permalink":"/2023/03/11/dispari\u021bia-b\u0103ncii"},"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Enjoy the process","permalink":"/2022/01/21/enjoy-the-process"}},"content":"Creating a schedule for your Amazon RDS instances and clusters can help you save money on running costs, and also ensure that your database is only running when it\'s needed.\\nIt applies mostly on not-prod environments, where you have multiple RDS instances and the cost of running them becomes a problem.\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\nThere are several ways to schedule your RDS instances, such as using the AWS Management Console, the AWS Command Line Interface (CLI), or a third-party tool. However, one of the most effective ways to schedule your RDS instances is by using AWS Lambda and CloudWatch Events.\\n\\nIn the above example, everything is created via CDK stack in TypeScript. The Lambda will stop all the instances and clusters which will be found in the AWS account and the region specified in the CDK config. The RDS instances and clusters could be filtered using the the DescribeDBInstances/DescribeDBClusters API in order to apply the scheduler on a specific instance/cluster.\\n\\n\\nFirst, we need to create an IAM role that has the necessary permissions to interact with the RDS service. We can do this using the CDK by creating a new IAM role and attaching a policy that grants access to the RDS service.\\nNext, we will create a Lambda function using the CDK. In the function, we will use the AWS SDK for JavaScript in Node.js to interact with the RDS service. We will use the describeDBInstances and describeDBClusters methods to get a list of all available RDS instances and clusters, and then we will use the startDBInstance, startDBCluster, stopDBInstance methods to start or stop the instances and clusters.\\nAfter that, we need to create a CloudWatch Event that triggers the Lambda function. We can do this by creating a new CloudWatch Event and defining a schedule for when the event should trigger. For example, we can set the event to trigger every day at 7 am, except on weekends.\\nFinally, we will deploy the CDK stack, and the Lambda function, IAM role, and CloudWatch Event will be created and configured in your AWS account.\\n\\nBy following this process, you can ensure that your RDS instances and clusters are only running when they are needed, thus reducing your running costs. It\'s important to test the function before applying it to production, also to monitor the function\'s performance and to make sure that it\'s working correctly.\\nIn summary, using AWS Lambda and CloudWatch Events to schedule your RDS instances and clusters is an effective and cost-efficient way to manage your RDS instances. It also allows you to take advantage of the scalability and flexibility of the AWS Lambda service, and easily automate the process of starting and stopping your RDS instances.\\n\\nHere is the CDK stack:\\n\\n```typescript\\n    import * as cdk from \'aws-cdk-lib\';\\n    import * as lambda from \'aws-cdk-lib/aws-lambda\';\\n    import * as events from \'aws-cdk-lib/aws-events\';\\n    import { aws_events_targets, CfnOutput, NestedStack } from \\"aws-cdk-lib\\";\\n    import { Construct } from \\"constructs\\";\\n    import * as iam from \'aws-cdk-lib/aws-iam\';\\n\\n    export class StartStopRdsStack extends cdk.NestedStack {\\n      constructor(scope: Construct, id: string, props?: cdk.StackProps) {\\n        super(scope, id, props);\\n\\n        // Create the Lambda function to start RDS\\n        const startRdsInstancesLambda = new lambda.Function(this, \'psb-rds-start-lambda\', {\\n          runtime: lambda.Runtime.NODEJS_14_X,\\n          functionName: \'psb-rds-start-stop-lambda\',\\n          code: lambda.Code.fromAsset(\\"./lib/assets/functions/start-stop-rds-lambda\\"),\\n          handler: \\"index.handler\\",\\n          environment: {\\n            \\"tag\\": \\"some-tag\\",\\n            \\"info\\": \\"Shared function for starting-stopping RDS instances\\"\\n          }\\n        });\\n\\n       // Assign role to lambda to access RDS\\n        startRdsInstancesLambda.addToRolePolicy(new iam.PolicyStatement({\\n          effect: iam.Effect.ALLOW,\\n          actions: [\\n            \\"rds:DescribeDBInstances\\",\\n            \\"rds:DescribeDBClusters\\",\\n            \\"rds:StartDBInstance\\",\\n            \\"rds:StartDBCluster\\",\\n            \\"rds:StopDBInstance\\",\\n            \\"rds:StopDBCluster\\"\\n          ],\\n          resources: [\\"*\\"]\\n        }));\\n\\n\\n        // Create the CloudWatch Event rule for starting RDS every day at 7 AM\\n        const startRdsInstancesRule = new events.Rule(this, \'psb-start-rds-instances-rule\', {\\n          schedule: events.Schedule.cron({\\n              minute: \'0\',\\n              hour: \'7\',\\n              month: \'*\',\\n              weekDay: \'MON-FRI\'\\n          }),\\n        });\\n        startRdsInstancesRule.addTarget(new aws_events_targets.LambdaFunction(startRdsInstancesLambda));\\n\\n        // Create  the CloudWatch Event rule for stopping RDS every day at 18 PM\\n        const stopRdsInstancesRule = new events.Rule(this, \'psb-stop-rds-instances-rule\', {\\n          schedule: events.Schedule.cron({\\n            minute: \'0\',\\n            hour: \'18\',\\n            month: \'*\',\\n            weekDay: \'MON-FRI\'\\n          }),\\n        });\\n        stopRdsInstancesRule.addTarget(new aws_events_targets.LambdaFunction(startRdsInstancesLambda));\\n      }\\n    }\\n\\n```\\n  \\n  \\n  Here is the Lambda function\\n  \\n  ```typescript\\n  import { Handler } from \'aws-lambda\';\\nimport * as AWS from \'aws-sdk\';\\n\\nconst rds = new AWS.RDS();\\n\\nenum InstanceStatus {\\n    STOPPED = \'stopped\',\\n    AVAILABLE = \'available\',\\n}\\n\\nexport const handler: Handler = async () => {\\n  try {\\n    const instances = await rds.describeDBInstances().promise();\\n    console.log(\'Found instances: \', instances.DBInstances);\\n\\n    if (instances.DBInstances) {\\n      for (const instance of instances.DBInstances) {\\n        const identifier = instance.DBInstanceIdentifier!;\\n        const instanceStatus = instance.DBInstanceStatus!;\\n\\n        console.log(`${identifier} status: `, instanceStatus);\\n\\n        if (instanceStatus === InstanceStatus.STOPPED) {\\n          console.log(`Starting DB Instance with identifier:  ${identifier}`);\\n          await rds.startDBInstance({ DBInstanceIdentifier: identifier }).promise();\\n        } else {\\n          console.log(`Stopping  DB Instance with identifier:  ${identifier}`);\\n          await rds.stopDBInstance({ DBInstanceIdentifier: identifier }).promise();\\n        }\\n      }\\n    }\\n\\n    const describeClusters = await rds.describeDBClusters().promise();\\n    console.log(\'Found clusters: \', describeClusters.DBClusters);\\n\\n    if (describeClusters.DBClusters) {\\n      for (const cluster of describeClusters.DBClusters) {\\n        const identifier = cluster.DBClusterIdentifier!;\\n        const instanceStatus = cluster.Status!;\\n\\n        console.log(`${cluster.DBClusterIdentifier} status: `, cluster.Status);\\n\\n        if (cluster.Status === InstanceStatus.STOPPED) {\\n          console.log(`Starting DB Cluster with identifier:  ${identifier}`);\\n          await rds.startDBCluster({ DBClusterIdentifier: identifier }).promise();\\n        } else {\\n          console.log(`Stopping  DB Cluster with identifier:  ${identifier}`);\\n          await rds.stopDBCluster({ DBClusterIdentifier: identifier }).promise();\\n        }\\n      }\\n    }\\n\\n    return {\\n      statusCode: 200,\\n      headers: {\\n        \'Content-Type\': \'application/json\',\\n      },\\n      body: JSON.stringify({ success: true }),\\n      isBase64Encoded: false,\\n    };\\n  } catch (error) {\\n    console.error(error);\\n    return {\\n      statusCode: 500,\\n      headers: {\\n        \'Content-Type\': \'application/json\',\\n      },\\n      body: JSON.stringify({ error: error }),\\n      isBase64Encoded: false,\\n    };\\n  }\\n};\\n  ```"},{"id":"/2022/01/21/enjoy-the-process","metadata":{"permalink":"/2022/01/21/enjoy-the-process","source":"@site/blog/2022-01-21-enjoy-the-process.md","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Enjoy the process","description":"As a software developer, I find great joy in creating new products. The process of bringing an idea to life is incredibly satisfying, and there is nothing quite like seeing your work in use by others.","date":"2022-01-21T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 21, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":1.215,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Alexandru Ilies"}],"frontMatter":{"layout":"post","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Enjoy the process","author":"Alexandru Ilies"},"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Amazon RDS Start-Stop Scheduler with CDK and TypeScript","permalink":"/2023/01/23/rds-start-stop-scheduler"},"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f","permalink":"/A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f"}},"content":"As a software developer, I find great joy in creating new products. The process of bringing an idea to life is incredibly satisfying, and there is nothing quite like seeing your work in use by others.\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\nOne of the things I love most about developing new products is the problem-solving aspect. Each project presents its own unique set of challenges, and finding the best solutions to those challenges is a constant source of inspiration and motivation for me.\\n\\nI also enjoy the collaborative nature of product development. Working with a team of talented individuals to bring a shared vision to life is incredibly rewarding. Whether it\'s bouncing ideas off of one another, contributing to code reviews, or simply sharing a laugh over a particularly tricky bug, the camaraderie and sense of shared accomplishment is a big part of what makes developing new products so enjoyable.\\n\\nAnother aspect that I find enjoyable is the opportunity to learn and grow. As technology and best practices are always evolving, I am always learning new skills and techniques that help me become a better developer. Additionally, the opportunity to experiment with new technologies and approaches is always exciting.\\n\\nIn short, developing new products is a challenging and rewarding experience that offers a sense of accomplishment, opportunities for problem-solving, collaboration, and learning. It\'s a great joy for me as a software developer, and it\'s what keeps me motivated to continue to push the boundaries of what\'s possible."},{"id":"A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f","metadata":{"permalink":"/A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f","source":"@site/blog/2018-05-22-a-java-dto-mapping-example.md","title":"\ud83d\ude80 A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f","description":"Originally written here","date":"2018-05-22T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 22, 2018","tags":[{"label":"java","permalink":"/tags/java"},{"label":"howto","permalink":"/tags/howto"}],"readingTime":3.995,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Alexandru Ilies"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f","title":"\ud83d\ude80 A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f","layout":"post","author":"Alexandru Ilies","tags":["java","howto"]},"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Enjoy the process","permalink":"/2022/01/21/enjoy-the-process"},"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 VPN Personal \xeen 3 minute","permalink":"/2018/04/20/vpn-personal-in-3-minute"}},"content":"Originally written [here](https://hackmajoris.medium.com/a-generic-dtos-mapping-in-java-11d649b8a486)\\n\\nSometimes you may need to use DTO\'s(Data Transfer Objects) in your application in order to hide some entity data(usually) in your REST\'full API. For instance: You have a User entity which has some fields: username, email, password, ID.\\nYou have an API which performs some CRUD operations on this entity and you want to hide user password at the moment when GET(only) operation is performed.\\nFor such a feature you need to have a DTO Entity where you exclude the password field from the base Entity. You need somehow to map all the attributes from base entity to DTO entity end vice-versa\\nand it is nice if you\'ll do this automatically without mapping the attributes manually.\\n\\nHere is how we can achieve this using ModelMapping...\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n## How to test\\n\\n* Download [repository](https://github.com/hackmajoris/java-dto-mapping)\\n\\n* Navigate terminal to the project root folder.\\n\\n* Run command \\n\\n     ```bash\\n      mvn install && mvn spring-boot:run\\n     ```\\n\\n### Project structure\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1036/format:webp/1*Dq96nIHWOe6DPoMl1Rg2GQ.png)\\n\\n\\n### User model\\n\\nHere we have a simple User class with some attributes.\\n\\n ```java\\npublic class User {\\n\\n    private int id;\\n    private String name;\\n    private String email;\\n    private String password;\\n\\n    public User() {}\\n\\n    public int getId() {\\n     return id;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void setId(int id) {\\n     this.id = id;\\n    }\\n\\n    public String getName() {\\n     return name;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void setName(String name) {\\n     this.name = name;\\n    }\\n\\n    public String getEmail() {\\n     return email;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void setEmail(String email) {\\n     this.email = email;\\n    }\\n\\n    public String getPassword() {\\n     return password;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void setPassword(String password) {\\n     this.password = password;\\n    }\\n\\n    @Override\\n    public String toString() {\\n     return \\"User{\\" +\\n     \\"id=\\" + id +\\n     \\", name=\'\\" + name + \'\\\\\'\' +\\n     \\", email=\'\\" + email + \'\\\\\'\' +\\n     \\", password=\'\\" + password + \'\\\\\'\' +\\n     \'}\';\\n     }\\n}\\n\\n ```\\n\\n### User service\\n\\nHere is a simple User service implementation. The database connection and data persistance is not the goal at this point.\\n\\n ```java\\n@Service\\npublic class UserService {\\n\\n   public DTOEntity createUser(){\\n    User user = new User();\\n    user.setId(1);\\n    user.setName(\\"User number 1\\");\\n    user.setEmail(\\"Email number 1\\");\\n    user.setPassword(\\"Password number 1\\");\\n\\n    return new DtoUtils().convertToDto(user, new UserCreateDTO());\\n   }\\n\\n   public DTOEntity readUser(){\\n    User user = new User();\\n    user.setId(1);\\n    user.setName(\\"User number 1\\");\\n    user.setEmail(\\"Email number 1\\");\\n    user.setPassword(\\"Password number 1\\");\\n\\n    return new DtoUtils().convertToDto(user, new UserReadDTO());\\n   }\\n\\n   public DTOEntity updateUser(DTOEntity userDTO) {\\n    User user = (User) new DtoUtils().convertToEntity(new User(), userDTO);\\n\\n    System.out.println(user.toString());\\n\\n    return new DtoUtils().convertToDto(user, new UserUpdateDTO());\\n   }\\n}\\n\\n ```\\n### TDO Utils \\n\\nThe important part here is this utility class: \\n\\n ```java\\npublic class DtoUtils {\\n   public DTOEntity convertToDto(Object obj, DTOEntity mapper) {\\n    return new ModelMapper().map(obj, mapper.getClass());\\n   }\\n\\n   public Object convertToEntity(Object obj, DTOEntity mapper) {\\n    return new ModelMapper().map(mapper, obj.getClass());\\n   }\\n}\\n\\n ```\\n\\nAs you can see, here we have two methods for in/out mapping. I tried to create them as generic is possible in order to user them for all entities.\\n\\nNow, the DTO\'s entities.\\n\\n### UserRead DTO\\n\\n ```java\\npublic class UserReadDTO implements DTOEntity {\\n\\n    private String name;\\n    private String email;\\n\\n    public UserReadDTO(){}\\n\\n    public String getName() {\\n     return name;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void setName(String name) {\\n     this.name = name;\\n    }\\n\\n    public String getEmail() {\\n     return email;\\n    }\\n\\n    public void setEmail(String email) {\\n     this.email = email;\\n    }\\n}\\n ```\\n\\nHere we implemented DTOEntity interface: \\n\\n ```java\\n public interface DTOEntity {}\\n ```\\n\\nin order to have a generic mapping. So all our DTO\'s will implement this interface.\\n\\n\\n!In this entity we excluded the password field.\\n\\n\\n### The User Controller\\n\\nNow, that we have all needed models and helpers, our controller looks in this way:\\n\\n ```java\\n@RestController\\n@RequestMapping(\\"api/\\")\\npublic class UserController {\\n\\n    private UserService updateService;\\n\\n    @Autowired\\n    public UserController(UserService updateService){\\n     this.updateService = updateService;\\n    }\\n\\n    @RequestMapping(value = \\"/create\\", method = RequestMethod.POST)\\n    public DTOEntity createPost(@RequestBody UserCreateDTO userCreateDTO) {  \\n     return updateService.createUser();\\n    }\\n\\n    @RequestMapping(value = \\"/list\\", method = RequestMethod.GET)\\n    public DTOEntity readUser() {\\n     return updateService.readUser();\\n    }\\n\\n    @RequestMapping(value = \\"/update\\", method = RequestMethod.PATCH)\\n    public DTOEntity updateUser(@RequestBody UserUpdateDTO userUpdateDTO) {\\n     return updateService.updateUser(userUpdateDTO);\\n    }\\n}\\n ```\\n\\n### See also the test cases:\\n\\n ```java\\npublic class UserDtoUnitTest {\\n\\n@Test\\npublic void userEntityToUserDto() {\\n\\n   // Given\\n   User user = new User();\\n   user.setId(1);\\n   user.setEmail(\\"user1@example.com\\");\\n   user.setName(\\"user1\\");\\n   user.setPassword(\\"user1Password\\");\\n\\n   // When\\n   UserCreateDTO userCreateDTO =  (UserCreateDTO) new DtoUtils().convertToDto(user, new UserCreateDTO());\\n\\n   // Then\\n   assertEquals(user.getEmail(), userCreateDTO.getEmail());\\n   assertEquals(user.getName(), userCreateDTO.getName());\\n   assertEquals(user.getPassword(), userCreateDTO.getPassword());\\n  }\\n\\n  @Test\\n  public void userDtoToUserEntity() {\\n   // Given\\n   UserCreateDTO userCreateDTO = new UserCreateDTO();\\n   userCreateDTO.setEmail(\\"user1@example.com\\");\\n   userCreateDTO.setName(\\"user1\\");\\n   userCreateDTO.setPassword(\\"user1Password\\");\\n\\n   // When\\n   User user =  (User) new DtoUtils().convertToEntity(new User(), userCreateDTO);\\n\\n   // Then\\n   assertEquals(user.getEmail(), userCreateDTO.getEmail());\\n   assertEquals(user.getName(), userCreateDTO.getName());\\n   assertEquals(user.getPassword(), userCreateDTO.getPassword());\\n  }\\n}\\n ```\\n \\n### Testing\\n\\n#### User creation\\n\\n ```bash\\n curl -X POST \\\\\\n http://localhost:8080/api/create \\\\\\n -H \'Cache-Control: no-cache\' \\\\\\n -H \'Content-Type: application/json\' \\\\\\n -d \'{\\"name\\":\\"User number 1\\",\\"email\\":\\"Email number 2\\", \\"password\\": \\"userPassword\\"}\'\\n ```\\n#### User update\\n ```bash\\n curl -X PATCH \\\\\\n http://localhost:8080/api/update \\\\\\n -H \'Cache-Control: no-cache\' \\\\\\n -H \'Content-Type: application/json\' \\\\\\n -d \'{\\"name\\":\\"User number 1\\",\\"email\\":\\"Email number 2\\", \\"password\\": \\"pass\\"}\'\\n ```\\n\\n### User read\\n ```bash\\n curl -X GET \\\\\\n http://localhost:8080/api/list \\\\\\n -H \'Cache-Control: no-cache\' \\\\\\n -H \'Content-Type: application/json\' \\\\\\n -d \'{\\"name\\":\\"User number 1\\",\\"email\\":\\"Email number 2\\", \\"password\\": \\"pass\\"}\'\\n ```"},{"id":"/2018/04/20/vpn-personal-in-3-minute","metadata":{"permalink":"/2018/04/20/vpn-personal-in-3-minute","source":"@site/blog/2018-04-20-vpn-personal-in-3-minute.md","title":"\ud83d\ude80 VPN Personal \xeen 3 minute","description":"De ce?","date":"2018-04-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 20, 2018","tags":[],"readingTime":4.305,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Alexandru Ilies"}],"frontMatter":{"layout":"post","title":"\ud83d\ude80 VPN Personal \xeen 3 minute","author":"Alexandru Ilies"},"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f","permalink":"/A Java DTO mapping example\ufe0f"},"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Despre Lightning Network","permalink":"/2018/01/29/despre-lightning-network"}},"content":"## De ce?\\nDac\u0103 ai ajuns s\u0103 cau\u021bi informa\u021bii despre VPN, cel mai probabil dore\u0219ti s\u0103 \xee\u021bi securizezi c\xe2t de c\xe2t prezenta ta pe Internet, fie c\u0103 ai motive evidente sau pur \u0219i simplu e\u0219ti un simplu utilizator de Internet. Oricare ar fi motivul - folosirea unui VPN este de neevitat, vedem imediat de ce.\\n\\nDe c\xe2te ori ai folosit o re\u021bea de Wireless, public\u0103, f\u0103r\u0103 nici o mic\u0103 b\u0103nuial\u0103 legat\u0103 de riscuri sau consecin\u021be? \\n\\nR\u0103spuns: de fiecare dat\u0103(cel mai probabil).\\nC\xe2t de mici sau c\xe2t de mari pot fi riscurile folosirii unui Wireless public, depinde de ac\u021biunile tale care le-ai f\u0103cut pe Internet, \xeen timp ce foloseai acea re\u021bea. Astfel de re\u021bele sunt cele mai des vulnerabile. Sunt zeci, sau sute de utilizatori care au acces direct la acea re\u021bea iar cafeneaua, ca proprietar al re\u021belei, de regul\u0103, nu este interesat\u0103 de securitate. De aceea, nu \xee\u021bi dore\u0219ti s\u0103 te treze\u0219ti f\u0103r\u0103 bani pe card, \xeen cazul \xeen care ai f\u0103cut o cump\u0103r\u0103tur\u0103 online \xeen timp ce erai conectat la acea re\u021bea. \\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\nPe l\xe2ng\u0103 partea de securitate \u0219i anonimitate pe Internet, VPN-ul \xee\u021bi ofer\u0103 acces la site-uri cenzurate pe teritoriul \xeen care te afli(de exemplu Spotify, p\xe2n\u0103 acum 2 luni - Romania), access la magazinele de aplica\u021bii (AppStore, GooglePlay) din alte regiuni \u0219i alte posibile facilit\u0103\u021bi de acest gen. \\n\\n## Cum?\\n\\nExist\u0103 zeci de aplica\u021bii care ofer\u0103 servicii VPN pentru mobile c\xe2t \u0219i pentru alte platforme. Cele mai evidente probleme pe care le ofer\u0103 sunt: pre\u021bul, anonimitatea, lipsa controlului asupra propriului trafic. Singurul serviciu de acest gen, \xeen care am \xeencredere este [TunellBear](https://www.tunnelbear.com/pricing).  Sugerez s\u0103-l folosi\u021bi \xeen cazul \xeen care ave\u021bi nevoie de un VPN \u0219i nu v\u0103 aranjez\u0103 solu\u021bia propus\u0103 mai jos. Acest serviciu ofer\u0103 500MB gratis, lunar, iar pentru un trafic nelimitat - pre\u021bul este de 10 USD. Mai jost o s\u0103 vedem cum putem ob\u021bine a\u0219a ceva cu resurse mai pu\u021bine.\\n\\n\\n! Solu\u021bia de mai jos este pentru utilizatorii de r\xe2nd. Nu necesit\u0103 cuno\u0219tin\u021be \xeen nici un domeniu. Necesit\u0103 doar dorin\u021ba de a te proteja atunci c\xe2nd folose\u0219ti Internet.\\n\\n### De ce avem nevoie:\\n\\n- Un cont pe [DigitalOcean](https://www.digitalocean.com)\\n- S\u0103 pornim un Droplet pe [DigitalOcean](https://www.digitalocean.com)\\n- S\u0103 configur\u0103m VPN-ul pe acel Droplet.\\n- S\u0103 configur\u0103m device-urile pentru a folosi acel VPN.\\n\\nS\u0103 \xeencepem.\\n\\n### Creare cont pe DigitalOcean.\\n\\nCel mai basic Droplet pe DigitalOcean - ne cost\u0103 5 USD/lun\u0103. Acesta are:\\n\\n- Memorie RAM: 1GB\\n- Disk: 25GB SSD\\n- Transfer: 1TB\\n- CPU: 1 Core\\n\\nCe ne intereseaz\u0103 aici este capacitatea de transfer - 1 TB / lun\u0103 este de cele mai multe ori \xeendeajuns pentru un utilizator mediu. \\n\\nPentru a primi 10 USD credit la \xeenregistrare, da-\u021bi click [aici](https://m.do.co/c/6f4b7837cd02). Acesta v\u0103 va oferi 2 luni de acces gratuit, \xeen cazul \xeen care nu ave\u021bi \xeenc\u0103 cont.\\n\\nMai departe.... \\n\\n1. Ap\u0103s\u0103m butonul - Create\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/89pf6jpt80qegem/1.png?raw=1)\\n\\n2. Alegem creare Droplet nou\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/1s8oxsfx5iaq1ck/2.png?raw=1)\\n\\n3. Select\u0103m One-click apps \\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/tuz4apyy2dnum62/3.png?raw=1)\\n\\n4.  Select\u0103m tipul\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/83ul7cctr7bjcw8/4.png?raw=1)\\n\\n5. Select\u0103m resursele\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/wxxc48xm0itv55z/5.png?raw=1)\\n\\n6. Select\u0103m loca\u021bia  \\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/q9jkwo36osl2jze/6.png?raw=1)\\n\\n7. D\u0103m un nume la host\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/xjoeztg9lf2gip4/7.png?raw=1)\\n\\n8. Acces\u0103m consola\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/o72r5v9dwxyb5nl/8.png?raw=1)\\n\\n9. Dup\u0103 ce am schimbat parola de accesare a Droplet-ului, scrim  urm\u0103toarea comand\u0103:\\n ```bash\\nCID=$(docker run -d --restart=always --privileged -p 1194:1194/udp -p 443:443/tcp jpetazzo/dockvpn)\\n ```\\nVa trebui s\u0103 a\u0219tepta\u021bi pentru a se desc\u0103rca toate dependen\u021bele.\\n\\nConsola o s\u0103 arate undeva a\u0219a:\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/ftl6co5y5wjg3rx/9.png?raw=1)\\n\\n10. Dup\u0103, scriem \xeen consol\u0103 comanda\\n ```bash\\n docker run -t -i -p 8080:8080 --volumes-from $CID jpetazzo/dockvpn serveconfig\\n ```\\nDup\u0103 executare, \xeen consol\u0103 vom vedea o adres\u0103, de genul: 0.0.0.0:8080 (La fiecare va fi diferit\u0103)\\n\\n11. Mergem \xeen Browser, \u0219i acces\u0103m acea adres\u0103.\\n\\nAcces\xe2nd resursa, \xeen mod normal, Browserul se va pl\xe2nge din cauza securit\u0103\u021bii. Ignor\u0103m acea pl\xe2ngere - descarcam fisierul.\\n\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/vsxw4ur59qsqe90/10.png?raw=1)\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/nokabrhe7q0sjh9/11.png?raw=1)\\n\\n\\nDup\u0103 desc\u0103rcare, redenumim fi\u0219ierul \xeen a\u0219a fel \xeenc\xe2t acesta s\u0103 aib\u0103 extensia .ovpn\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/4p1xny119pbs5je/12.png?raw=1)\\n\\n12. Desc\u0103rc\u0103m aplica\u021bia-client pentru platforma pe care o folosim. Sunt diferite aplica\u021bii de genul VPN-client prin care ne-am putea conecta la serverul de VPN creat mai sus. Vom folosi [OpenVPN](https://openvpn.net/index.php/open-source/downloads.html). Simplu de folosit \u0219i are \u0219i suport pentru toate platformele. Mai jos, o s\u0103 vedem cum putem configura clientul pe macOS \u0219i iOS. Pe Windows, Linux, Android, etc - e aceea\u0219i procedur\u0103.\\n13. [Desc\u0103rc\u0103m](https://openvpn.net/index.php/open-source/downloads.html) clientul dac\u0103 nu am f\u0103cut-o \u0219i \xeei d\u0103m fi\u0219ierul de .ovpn desc\u0103rcat anterior, dup\u0103 care ne conect\u0103m.\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/yeoivmd8ldxdtki/13.png?raw=1)\\n\\n14. Dup\u0103 o conexiune reu\u0219it\u0103, navig\u0103m pe [whatismyipaddress.com](https://whatismyipaddress.com) \u0219i convingem c\u0103 VPN-ul \xee\u0219i face treaba. \ud83d\ude0a\\n\\n\\n### Configurare VPN client - iOS\\n\\n- Instal\u0103m [OpenVPN Connect](https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/openvpn-connect/id590379981?mt=8)\\n- Deschidem aplica\u021bia, \u0219i introducem acela\u0219i adres\u0103 de IP:\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/wjb0akzuha2t3id/14.png?raw=1)\\n- Deschidem fi\u0219ierul cu applica\u021bia OpenVPN\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/gwqfmzj8j3sz6x6/15.jpg?raw=1)\\n- Instal\u0103m certificatul \\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/0knsibq6cajhsfc/16.jpg?raw=1)\\n- Ne conect\u0103m\\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/z5ckietmjora1pg/17.jpg?raw=1)\\n- Verific\u0103m pe [whatismyipaddress.com](https://whatismyipaddress.com)\\n\\n\\n## Important\\nDup\u0103 ce am configurat toate device-urile, ne \xeentoarcem la consola Dropletului de pe DigitalOcean, \u0219i d\u0103m un Ctrl/Cmd+c pentru a opri ultimul container pornit, \xeen a\u0219a fel, nimeni nu va mai putea desc\u0103rca fi\u0219ierul(.ovpn) desc\u0103rcat mai sus dac\u0103 va accesa IP-ul Droplet-ului. \\n\\n## Cat te cost\u0103?\\nSolu\u021bia dat\u0103 poate fi hostat\u0103 \u0219i pe un server local, dac\u0103 acesta exist\u0103. Dac\u0103 nu - metoda descris\u0103 mai sus te va costa 5 USD/lun\u0103(nu uita - primele 2 luni le ai gratuit dac\u0103 te-ai \xeenregistrat folosind link-ul men\u021bionat mai sus).  \\n\\nCam asta este tot, \\n\\nMay the security be with you. \ud83d\ude0b"},{"id":"/2018/01/29/despre-lightning-network","metadata":{"permalink":"/2018/01/29/despre-lightning-network","source":"@site/blog/2018-01-29-despre-lightning-network.md","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Despre Lightning Network","description":"Articol tradus. Sursa original\u0103","date":"2018-01-29T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 29, 2018","tags":[],"readingTime":19.02,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Alexandru Ilies"}],"frontMatter":{"layout":"post","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Despre Lightning Network","author":"Alexandru Ilies"},"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 VPN Personal \xeen 3 minute","permalink":"/2018/04/20/vpn-personal-in-3-minute"},"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Macbook Upgrade. First Impressions","permalink":"/2018/01/11/macbook-upgrade-first-impresions"}},"content":"Articol tradus. Sursa [original\u0103](https://medium.com/@x0100/%EF%B8%8Flightning-network-7c618c9cd68)\\n\\nLighting Network = LN\\n\\n\xcen partea 0 vom vedea, de ce este nevoie de a\u0219a ceva. \\n\xcen partea 1 vom explica cum se desf\u0103\u0219oar\u0103 toate pl\u0103\u021bile \xeen re\u021beaua Bitcoin, Lightning Network \u0219i problemele care se reg\u0103sesc. \xcen partea 2 vom introduce componentele de baz\u0103 din care e construit LN. \xcen partea 3, \xeen sf\xe2r\u0219it vom descrie \xeen detaliu cum sunt procesate pl\u0103\u021bile \xeen protocolul LN. \xcen a 4 parte, \xeen mod rapid vom vorbi despre criticile care se reg\u0103sesc \u0219i comisionale existente. \xcen partea 5, vom face un mic sumar.\\n\\n\\n!\xcen mod con\u0219tient renun\u021b/simplific unele momente tehnice. \xcenc\u0103 nu sunt expert \u0219i pot s\u0103 m\u0103 \xeen\u0219el \xeen unele afirm\u0103ri.\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## 0. De ce?\\n**Bitcoin Blockchain** - are la baz\u0103 o baz\u0103 date descentralizat\u0103, \xeen care se salveaz\u0103 toate tranzac\u021biile din re\u021beaua Bitcoin. P\xe2na aici, \u201dtoate tranzac\u021biile\u201d este o parte destul de fundamental\u0103 la acest protocol. Ca \xeentreg sistem s\u0103 fie \xeentradev\u0103r descentralizat, \u0219i totodat\u0103 func\u021bioneze f\u0103r\u0103 vreo oarecare eroare, trebuie, ca toate miile de noduri din re\u021bea s\u0103 re-verifice \u0219i s\u0103 salveze toate tranzac\u021biile. Acest lucru, \xeen mod clar, nu duce la o scalare: Blockchain ocup\u0103 zeci de Gigabytes pe disk, minerii folosesc mai mult curent dec\xe2t are nevoie unele \u021b\u0103ri, blocurile sunt suprasolicitate, comisioanele cresc, oamenii \xeenjur\u0103 \u0219i fac fork la Bitcoin. Din aceaste cauze, la moment, \xeen mod activ se construiesc solu\u021bii alternative. Una dintre aceste solu\u021bii este Lightning Network.\\n\\n<blockquote>\\n<p lang=\\"en\\" dir=\\"ltr\\">Q: When will the Lightning Network be rolled out? A: The rollout has already begun. This is an iterative distributed learning process; it&#39;s unlikely there will be a single point in time at which we say LN is &quot;deployed&quot; because it will grow organically. Software is never finished.</p>&mdash; Jameson Lopp (@lopp) <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/lopp/status/947808940255006726?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">January 1, 2018</a>\\n</blockquote>\\n\\n### 1. Ideea\\n\\nIdea de solu\u021bionare a problemei de la nivelului doi (second layer solution), la care se refer\u0103 LN, sun\u0103 foarte simplu:\\n\\n<blockquote>\\n\xcen loc s\u0103 se salveze \u0219i s\u0103 se verifice toate tranzac\u021biile \xeen Blokchain, vom realiza o mare parte din pl\u0103\u021bi \xeen afara re\u021belei Blockchain, iar \xeen Blockchain vom sincroniza din timp \xeen timp balan\u021bele \u0219i vom rezolva conflictele. De fun\u021bionat toate acestea vor func\u021biona, ca deobicei cu ajutorul criptomagiei.\\n</blockquote>\\n\\nSun\u0103 bine, \xeens\u0103 nu \u0219tim cum toate acestea func\u021bioneaz\u0103.\\n### 1.1. Canalul de plat\u0103\\nS\u0103 \xeencepem prin a simplifica via\u021ba a dou\u0103 persoane, Alisa \u0219i Bob, care foarte des se pl\u0103tesc \xeentre ei. Se ofer\u0103 urm\u0103toarea schema:\\n\\n1. Alisa \u0219i Bob trimit depozituri la adresa o adres\u0103 comun\u0103 care se administreaz\u0103 cu ajutorul a dou\u0103 chei private.\\n2. Fiecare din ei, creaz\u0103 o tranzac\u021bie special\u0103 - Smart Contract(da, Bitcoin dispune de Smart-Contracts, despre asta \xeen partea urm\u0103toare). Aceast\u0103 tranzac\u021bie este corect\u0103, dar \xeenc\u0103 nu este scris\u0103 \xeen Blochain.\\n3. De la \xeenceput, tranzac\u021bia con\u021bine informa\u021bie conform c\u0103reia, Alisa \u0219i Bob pot lua \xeenapoi depozitele lor.\\n4. Cand Alisa se achit\u0103 cu Bob, printr-o \xeen\u021belegere comun\u0103 -updateaz\u0103 informa\u021bia din aceste tranzac\u021bii. Alisa accept\u0103 s\u0103 primeasc\u0103 mai pu\u021bin\u0103 valoare din propriul depozit, iar Bob - mai mult\u0103. Defapt, aceste tranzac\u021bii reprezint\u0103 niste obliga\u021biuni(IOU, I owe you)\\n5. \xcen a\u0219a mod, ei pot schimba \xeentre ei sume nu foarte mari(\xeen limitele depozitelor lor), m\u0103car p\xe2n\u0103 la nesf\xe2r\u0219it.\\n6. La un anumit moment, oricare din p\u0103r\u021bi, poate s\u0103 cear\u0103 s\u0103 se achite pentru totdeauna. Atunci Lisa(sau Bob) pur \u0219i simplu \xeenscriu tranzac\u021bia final\u0103 \xeen Blockchain-ul principal \u0219i primesc suma depozitului \xeempreun\u0103 cu suma provenit\u0103 din pl\u0103\u021bile care au fost f\u0103cute c\u0103tre acest depozit. \\n\\nPunctele 1-3 din aceast\u0103 schem\u0103 se numesc deschiderea canalului de pl\u0103t\u0103/pl\u0103\u021bi(payment channel). Punctele 4 \u0219i 5 - folosirea canalului. Punctul 6 - \xeenchiderea canalului de plat\u0103/pl\u0103\u021bi.\\n\\n\\n<blockquote>\\n\ud83d\udc4d \xcen blockchain se \xeenscriu doar dou\u0103 tranzac\u021bii: tranzac\u021bia de depozitare, \xeen care are loc deschiderea canalului de plat\u0103 \u0219i tranzac\u021bia final\u0103(\xeenchiderea canalului). Toate tranzac\u021biile interemediare dintre aceste dou\u0103 tranzac\u021bii nu se folosesc de Blockchain \u0219i nu sunt salvate \xeen acesta, de aceea acestea sunt f\u0103cute f\u0103r\u0103 nici un cost(comision) \u0219i sunt momentane.\\n</blockquote>\\n\\n\\n\\n### 1.2. Re\u021beaua de canale de plat\u0103\\n\\nCanalele de pl\u0103\u021bi \xeentre dou\u0103 persoane - nu este ceva foarte util. La urma urmei, cu marea majoritate a oamenilor noi nu facem tranzac\u021bii regulare. Dar...\\n<blockquote>\\n\ud83d\udca1 Cand canalele de plat\u0103 formeaz\u0103 o re\u021bea, se ive\u0219te posibilitatea de a face pl\u0103\u021bi \xeentre fiecare utilizator al re\u021belei, c\u0103tre care exist\u0103 o leg\u0103tur\u0103 \xeen graful acestei re\u021bele(chiar dac\u0103 ei nu au leg\u0103tur\u0103 direct\u0103 unul cu altul). Aceasta \u0219i este ideea de baz\u0103 a Lighting Network.\\n</blockquote>\\n\\nA\u0219a arat\u0103 graful canalelor de plat\u0103, \xeen momentul 22.01.2018: (https://lnmainnet.gaben.win).\\n![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*vYgP4rEOttWssox5l-LGig.png)\\n\\n\xcen principiu, analog protocolului TCP, unui om simplu \xeei este \xeendeajuns s\u0103 aib\u0103 doar un singur canal deschis, ca acesta s\u0103 poat\u0103 s\u0103 utilizeze tranzac\u021bii cu oricine. Desigur, este nevoie s\u0103 se caute \u0219i segmentul cel mai optim \xeentre doi utilizatori, \u0219i mai trebuie cumva s\u0103 se motiveze participan\u021bii re\u021belei ca ace\u0219tia s\u0103 verifice tranzac\u021biile str\u0103ine. Dar, sa \xeencepem cu problema de baz\u0103: problema \xeencrederii.\\n\\n### 1.3. Problema \xeencrederii\\nCum se \xeent\xe2mpl\u0103 des \xeen criptografie, sistema canalelor de plat\u0103 este foarte simplu de imaginat, dac\u0103 toate par\u021bile au \xeencredere \xeentre ele. Nu este nevoie s\u0103 \xeengr\u0103dim gr\u0103dina cu depozite, chei private, tranzac\u021bii speciale. Se poate simplu de scris doar cui \u0219i cu c\xe2t este cineva dator.\\nUrm\u0103torul lucru de \xeen\u021beles: cum putem realiza un canal de pl\u0103\u021bi f\u0103r\u0103 a avea \xeencredere \xeentre par\u021bi?\\nProblemele de baz\u0103 for fi trei.\\n\\n1. Ambele depozite, ale Alisei \u0219i Bob se afl\u0103 \xeentrun portofel virtual comun. Dac\u0103 Bob nu va fi deacord s\u0103 semneze tranzac\u021bia, cum Alisa \xee\u0219i va \xeentoarce depozitul ei?\\n2. \xcen procesul de calculare, sunt create multiple versiuni ale oblica\u021biunilor. S\u0103 presupunem c\u0103, practic, Alisa \xeel pl\u0103te\u0219te pe Bob. Atunci, \xeen versiunea final\u0103 a tranzac\u021biei, Bob va primi un depozit mai mare dec\xe2t depozitul lui ini\u021bial iar Alisa - mai pu\u021bin. Dar Alisa poate \xeen\u0219ela \u0219i poate \xeenscrie singur\u0103 \xeen Blockchain prima versiune valid\u0103 a tranzac\u021biei, ca \u0219i cum Bob niciodat\u0103 nu a primit bani. Cu ce va r\u0103m\xe2ne Bob?\\n3. Dac\u0103 Alisa \u0219i Bob, transfer\u0103 banii prin re\u021bea folosind o a treia persoan\u0103 - Victor, atunci cum ei pot fi siguri c\u0103 Victor \xeentradev\u0103r va transmite banii \u0219i nu \xeei va lua lui?\\n\\nS\u0103 numim aceste probleme corespunz\u0103tor: \\n\\n- problema depozitului comun\\n- problema ultimei tranzac\u021bii\\n- problema persoanei ter\u021be\\n\\n\\n## 2. Smart-contractsz`~~aqwa`=-[p0o9az`~ZA;./\\"|\\n>\u2264\\nBitcoin are suport pentru un limbaj simplu al smart-contractelor - Script. \xcen fiecare tranzac\u021bie Bitcoin exist\u0103 un c\xe2mp special, care con\u021bine un script scris \xeen acest limbaj. Acest script verific\u0103, dup\u0103 aplicarea a c\u0103ror reguli, ie\u0219irea tranzac\u021biei poate fi folosit\u0103.\\n\u201dFolosirea ie\u0219irei tranzac\u021biei A\u201d - este un mod mult mai corect tehnic spus \u201dfolosirea banilor din adresa/portofelul K, unde ace\u0219tia au fost depu\u0219i cu ajutorul tranzac\u021biei A\u201d\\n\\n<blockquote>\\n\u261d \xcen compara\u021bie, de exemplu, cu Ethereum, posibilit\u0103\u021bile smart-contractelor Bitcoin sunt cu mult mai limitate. Este legat acest lucru de Script, \u0219i anume c\u0103 acesta nu este destul pentru Turing. De exemplu, \xeen acesta nu se poate folosi cicluri/recursivitate \u0219i nu se poate crea variabile(lipsa memoriei).\\n</blockquote>\\n\\nS\u0103 vedem cele mai importante opera\u021bii ale acestui limbaj.\\n\\n### 2.1 Autoriza\u021bia\\nProbail, partea cea mai standard a oric\u0103rei tranzac\u021bii - este verificarea semn\u0103turii. S\u0103 presupunem c\u0103 tranzac\u021bia A, transfer\u0103 resurse la o oarecare adres\u0103 K. Ca s\u0103 fie cheltuite resursele din K, trebuie s\u0103 se demonstreze de\u021binerea cheii(cheia privat\u0103). De acest lucru r\u0103spunde opera\u021bia **OP_CheckSig**. Dar, dup\u0103 dorin\u021b\u0103, se poate verifica \u0219i ceva adaug\u0103tor. De exemplu, se poate verifica, c\u0103 persoana de\u021bine un num\u0103r secret, iar hash-ul este egal cu acel num\u0103r. Pentru aceasta, este nevoie de dou\u0103 opera\u021biuni: **OP_SHA256**(cite\u0219te hash-ul) \u0219i **OP_EqualVerify**(verific\u0103 egalitatea). De ce avem nevoie de toate acestea, va fi clar \xeen partea 4.\\n\\n### 2.2. Cooperarea\\nUn alt exemplu simplu de smart-contract la Bitcoin se bazeaz\u0103 pe opera\u021bia **OP_CheckMultiSig**. Aceasta permite s\u0103 se foloseasc\u0103 resursele doar prin semnarea c\xe2torva chei predefinite. Pe acest principiu fun\u021bioneaz\u0103 a\u0219a spusele \u201dmultiple signature wallets\u201d. La fel ca \u0219i celula unei b\u0103nci, care este \xeencuiat\u0103 cu dou\u0103 chei, una afl\xe2ndu-se la angajatorul b\u0103ncii iar alta la client.\\n### 2.3. Perioadele\\nBitcoin are suport \u0219i pentru opera\u021bia **OP_CheckSequesnceVerify**, care permite folosirea resurselor doar peste un num\u0103r fix de blocuri. De exemplu, aceasta permite educarea oamenilor, care nu pot salva resursele. Blockchain este mai eficient dec\xe2t oricare cont de economii: dac\u0103 utilizatorul a decis s\u0103 \xeenghe\u021be suma acumulat\u0103 pe o anumit\u0103 perioad\u0103, aceast\u0103 sum\u0103 va fi \xeenghe\u021bat\u0103 garantat. Dar, pe l\xe2ng\u0103 acest scenariu, **OP_CheckSequenceVerify**, \u0219i alte componente, \xeen mod activ se folosesc pentru realizarea canalelor de pl\u0103\u021bi.\\n\\n## 3. Realizarea canalului\\nAcum, c\xe2nd toate blocurile de control sunt la locul lor, se poate descrie unele detalii ale func\u021bion\u0103rii canalului de plat\u0103.  Defapt, unele imagin\u0103ri ale canalului de pl\u0103\u021bi, au fost descrise \xeenc\u0103 de Satoshi. Eu ma voi axa mai mult pe specifica\u021bia, care se nume\u0219te Poon-Dryja payment channels(dup\u0103 p\u0103rerea autorilor principali Lightning Network).\\n\\n### 3.1. Deschiderea canalului\\n1. Alisa \u0219i Bob creaz\u0103 tranzac\u021bii, care depun resursele \xeentr-o adres\u0103 de depozit comun. S\u0103 presupunem c\u0103 X bitcoins se transfer\u0103 din portofelul Alisei, \u0219i Y - din portofelul lui Bob. Resursele din depozitul comun pot fi folosite doar prin semnarea \xeempreun\u0103 a cheilor private ale Alisei \u0219i Bob. (OP_CheckMultiSig). \\n2. Primul truc, se eviden\u021biaz\u0103 prin aceea c\u0103 ei \xeenc\u0103 NU semneaz\u0103 \u0219i NU transmit tranzac\u021bia \xeen Blockchain(dealtfel, Bob o poate min\u021bi pe Lisa \u0219i poate s\u0103-i \xeenghe\u021be rezursele pe ve\u0219nicie).)\\n3. \xcen loc de acestea, Alisa \u0219i Bob creaz\u0103 dou\u0103 noi tranzac\u021bii de retur a depozitului initial. Intrarea acestor tranzac\u021bii sunt resursele din depozitul comun(ie\u0219irea tranzac\u021biei 0). Ie\u0219iri ale tranzac\u021biilor sunt dou\u0103: X se duce \xeenapoi la adresa Alisei, Y - la adresa lui Bob. \xcen realitate, toate acestea sunt un pic mai dificile, dar despre asta, un pic mai t\xe2rziu.\\n4. Mai departe, Bob, semneaz\u0103 tranzac\u021bia A1 \u0219i o transmite c\u0103tre Alisa. Alisa semneaz\u0103 tranzac\u021bia B1 \u0219i o trimite lui Bob.\\n5. \xcen acest moment, tranzac\u021bia de depunere a depozitului, se poate \xeenscrie \xeen Blockchain, nimeni nu minte. Dac\u0103 Bob va fi deacord s\u0103 coopereze, Alisa oric\xe2nd poate semna tranzac\u021bia A1, s\u0103 o \xeenscrie \xeen Blockchain \u0219i s\u0103 ob\u021bin\u0103 depozitul acesteia \xeenapoi.\\n\\n\xcen acest moment \u201dproblema depozitului comun\u201d este rezolvat\u0103. Deschiderea canalului de plat\u0103 poate ave loc f\u0103r\u0103 a avea \xeencredere \xeen cealalt\u0103 persoan\u0103.\\n<blockquote>\\n\u261d Un fapt interesant. \xcenc\u0103 cu jum\u0103tate de an \xeen urm\u0103(\xeenainte de a se introduce SegWit) semnarea tranzac\u021biilor neconfirmate(punctul 4) avea loc mult mai greu, din cauza problemei maleabilitat\u0103\u021bii(transaction malleability)\\n</blockquote>\\n\\n### 3.2 Folosirea canalului\\nPl\u0103\u021bile din interiourul canalului se realizeaz\u0103 defapt prin re-rescrierea tranzac\u021biei A1 \u0219i B1 \xeen noi tranzac\u021bii.\\n\\n1. Alisa \xeel pl\u0103te\u0219te pe Bob pentru o cafea, care cost\u0103 C.\\n2. Tot Alisa, este deacord c\u0103, la \xeenchiderea canalului de plat\u0103 ea va lua \xeenapoi, nu suma depusa la \xeenceput X, ci X\' = (X - C).\\n3.  Iar Bob: Y\' = (Y + C).\\n\\nDeasemenea, noile tranzac\u021bii A2 \u0219i B2 vor ar\u0103ta la fel ca A1 \u0219i B1, doar c\u0103 cu sume noi. Fiecare din p\u0103r\u021bi, poate \xeen orice moment s\u0103 \xeenchid\u0103 canalul de plat\u0103, scriind ultima versiune a tranzac\u021biei \xeen Blockchain.\\n\\nCum ne asigur\u0103m c\u0103 Alisa nu va scrie \xeen Blockchain tranzac\u021bia A1  \xeen loc de tranzac\u021bia A2? Pentru aceasta, exista \xeenc\u0103 un truc.\\n\\n\\n1. De fiecare dat\u0103 c\xe2nd Alisa \u0219i Bob creaz\u0103 noi tranzac\u021bii, ei aleg o cheie privat\u0103 de unic\u0103 folosin\u021b\u0103, de care au nevoie ca s\u0103 poat\u0103 lua depozitul \xeenapoi(OP_CheckSig).\\n2. La fiecare plat\u0103 i, Alisa \xeei va ar\u0103ta lui Bob cheia privat\u0103 precedent\u0103 AK(i-1), \u0219i va crea o nou\u0103 cheie AKi pentru noua tranzac\u021bie. Bob nu va accepta plata f\u0103ra cheia anterioar\u0103.\\n3. Dac\u0103 Bob \u0219tie cheia, atunci acesta poate cheltui to\u021bi banii Alisei, doar dac\u0103 Alisa va decide s\u0103 \xeenscrie tranzac\u021bia gre\u0219it\u0103 \xeen Blockchain.\\n4. \xcen a\u0219a fel, Alisa \xeentodeauna este interesat\u0103 de a \xeenscrie \xeen Blockchain tranzac\u021bia corect\u0103, adic\u0103 utlima.\\n\\n*Modificare minor\u0103*\\nPentru ca Bob s\u0103 aib\u0103 posibilitatea s\u0103 dispute tranzac\u021bia cu Alisa \u0219i s\u0103 ob\u021bin\u0103 cheia acesteia, Bob are nevoie de timp. De aceea, Alisa, va ob\u021bine depozitul ei nu \xeen acela\u0219i timp, dar dup\u0103 c\xe2teva blocuri T(OP_CheckSequenceVerify). De exemplu, peste 48 blocuri, adic\u0103 peste 8 ore.\\n\\n\\nDac\u0103 Alisa semneaz\u0103 una din tranzac\u021biile ei(ele sunt semnate deja de Bob), \u0219i transmite aceast\u0103 tranzac\u021bie \xeen Blockchain, atunci pot avea loc dou\u0103 scenarii.\\n\\n1. Alisa emite tranzac\u021bia final\u0103 => Bob nu cunoa\u0219te utlima cheie a Alisei Aki. Aceasta este o \xeenchidere corect\u0103 a canalului, to\u021bi trebuie s\u0103 primeasc\u0103 banii lor \xeenapoi. Alisa \xeei va primi peste ceva timp.\\n2. Alisa \xeencearc\u0103 s\u0103 semneze tranzac\u021bia veche \xeen loc de cea nou\u0103, final\u0103 => Alisa \xeencearc\u0103 s\u0103-l mint\u0103 pe Bob. \xcen acest caz, Bob cunoa\u0219te cheia lui Alisa \u0219i acesta poate s\u0103 o foloseasc\u0103 pentru a primi toat\u0103 suma Alisei. Este clar c\u0103, Alisa nu este interesat\u0103 \xeen acest scenariu.\\n\\nA\u0219adar, \u201dproblema ultimei tranzac\u021bii\u201d este la fel - rezolvat\u0103 \u0219i canalul de comunicare \xeentre dou\u0103 persoane este \xeen regul\u0103. Acum, deasemenea, devin evidente c\xe2teva avantaje \u0219i neajunsuri.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc4d **Avanteje:**\\n\\n1. Pl\u0103\u021bile din interiorul canalului sunt instante \u0219i gratis, ele nu duc la solicitarea Blockchain-ului principal. \\n2. P\u0103r\u021bile nu sunt obligate s\u0103 aib\u0103 \xeencredere una \xeen alta.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc4e **Neajunsuri**\\n\\n1. Depozitele sunt blocate pe toat\u0103 perioada existen\u021bii canalului.\\n2. Fiecare dintre p\u0103r\u021bi, trebuie periodic s\u0103 se iveasc\u0103 online(cel pu\u021bin o dat\u0103-n T)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc4c \xcen realitate, ambele neajunsuri sunt necesare pentru canalele de pl\u0103\u021bi \xeentre dou\u0103 persoane, dar nu prea sunt importante pentru LN. Primul neajuns \xeenceteaz\u0103 s\u0103 mai fie neajuns dac\u0103 un canal de pl\u0103\u021bi poate fi folosit pentru tranzac\u021bii cu alte persoane.\\nAl doilea neajuns lipse\u0219te \xeen LN, a\u0219a cum verificarea corectitudinei poate fi f\u0103cut\u0103 de oricare utilizator al re\u021belei( dac\u0103 Vasile va observa \u021beapa Alisei, atunci acesta va \xeemp\u0103r\u021bi cu Bob valoarea confiscat\u0103.\\n\\n## 4. Lightning Network\\n\\n### 4.1. Canalul de pl\u0103\u021bi printr-o persoan\u0103 ter\u021b\u0103\\n\\nS\u0103 presupunem acum c\u0103 Alisa \u0219i Bob nu au un canal deschis \xeentre ei, dar ei, ambii au un canal deschis cu Victor. Alisa poate f\u0103r\u0103 probleme s\u0103 trimit\u0103 bani lui Victor, iar Victor f\u0103r\u0103 probleme poate trimite banii lui Bob.\\nDar, cum s\u0103 fim siguri, c\u0103 Victor, ob\u021bin\xe2nd banii, \xeentradev\u0103r \xeei va trimite mai departe lui Bob?\\n\\n\xcen realitate, ideea este foarte similar\u0103 cu trucul anterior, doar c\u0103 \xeen loc de cheile de unic\u0103 folosin\u021b\u0103 se folose\u0219te un oarecare num\u0103r secret.\\n\\n1. Bob genereaz\u0103 un num\u0103r secret S, hash-ul al acestei chei HS \u0219i transmite aceast\u0103 informa\u021bie Alisei. HS \xeen acest caz poate fi folosit ca un bon de plat\u0103 virtual.\\n2. Alisa creaz\u0103 tranzac\u021bia AV, care transmite banii lui Victor, numai \xeen cazul \xeen care Victor va oferi num\u0103rul secret S. Pentru aceasta, Alisa folose\u0219te un script, care verific\u0103 egalitatea hash-ului oferit de num\u0103rul \u0219i valoarea HS(aici se folose\u0219te opera\u021bia OP_SHA256 \u0219i OP_EqualVerify).\\n3. Victor creaz\u0103 o tranzac\u021bie analog VB, care transmite banii lui Bob, doar \xeen cazul \xeen care Bob va prezenta num\u0103rul secret.\\n4. Bob vede c\u0103 poate primi bani de la Victor, \u0219i \xeei arat\u0103 acestuia num\u0103rul secret S. Acum, Victor poate demonstra c\u0103 acesta a transmis banii lui Bob.\\n\\nAici sunt c\xe2teva variante \xeen care scenariile pot avea loc:\\n\\n1. \xcenainte de toate, Victor nu are nici un sens s\u0103 o mint\u0103 pe Alisa. El nu poate s\u0103 nu transmit\u0103 banii lui Bob, deoarece, dealtfel, Victor oricum nu va primi bani de la Alisa.\\n2. \xcens\u0103 Bob, poate s\u0103 decid\u0103 s\u0103-l mint\u0103 pe Victor \u0219i s\u0103 nu-i dea acestuia num\u0103rul secret. Pe l\xe2ng\u0103 asta, el poate \xeenchide canalul cu Victor \u0219i s\u0103 \xeenscrie \xeen blockchain tranzac\u021bia VB. \xcens\u0103, pentru primirea banilor, el oricum este nevoit s\u0103 arate  num\u0103rul lui secret, \u0219i aici - Victor \xeel va recunoa\u0219te.\\n\\nAici exist\u0103 c\xe2teva nuan\u021be, legate de timpul \xeen care Alisa, Bob \u0219i Victor pot rezolva conflictele. Dar, aceasta este o tem\u0103 mult prea tehnic\u0103. Dac\u0103 sunte\u021bi interesa\u021bi - Google it (Time-Locked Contracts or HTLCs).\\n\\n\\n## 4.2. Rutarea\\n\\n\xcen practic\u0103, Alisa \u0219i Bob pot fi lega\u021bi \xeentre ei nu prin cunoscutul lor comun - Victor, ci prin c\xe2\u021biva necunoscu\u021bi intermediari din \xeentreaga lume. Problema c\u0103ut\u0103rii celui mai scurt drum \xeen graf, \xeen re\u021bea, se nume\u0219te problema rut\u0103rii.\\n\\n![](https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*933GpxVj8PzBVPMQGbDeng.png)\\n(\xcemp\u0103r\u021birea geografic\u0103 a nodurilor \xeen re\u021beaua de test)\\nPhoto by: https://explorer.acinq.co/#/)\\n\\nProblema rut\u0103rii, \xeen realitate este o ramur\u0103 \xeen care se fac cercet\u0103ri active \xeen acest moment. Alegerea drumului optim \xeen graf depinde de mai mul\u021bi factori dinamici: num\u0103rul de noduri, topologia re\u021belei, capacitatea canalului de pl\u0103\u021bi, comisia nodurilor intermediare.\\n\\nCa s\u0103 nu intr\u0103m \xeen detalii, c\u0103utarea drumului \u0219i transmiterea pl\u0103\u021bilor \xeen LN se realizeaz\u0103 pe baza Onion Routing - tehnologia rasp\xe2ndirii informa\u021biei \xeen mod anonim, \xeen re\u021belele peer-to-peer.  \xcen acest fel, de exemplu, func\u021bioneaz\u0103 Tor.\\n\\n\\nTotul este descentralizat, tot traficul este criptat. Nimeni nu \u0219tie de la cine \u0219i c\u0103tre cine, vin \u0219i se duc banii. De aici, \xeenc\u0103 un avantaj.\\n\\n\\n\ud83d\udc4d **Avantaj**:\\nRe\u021beaua LN este cu mult mai anonim\u0103, dec\xe2t \xeens\u0103\u0219i el - Bitcoin.\\n\xcen primul r\xe2nd, persoanele care fac pl\u0103\u021bi \xeentre ei, sunt v\u0103zute doar de c\xe2\u021biva membri ai re\u021belei. \xcen al doilea r\xe2nd, chiar \u0219i \xeentre membrii re\u021belei, doar primul \u0219i ultimul \u0219tie exact, de la cine \u0219i c\u0103tre cine vin \u0219i se transmit banii.\\n\\n### 4.3. Comisioanele\\nR\u0103m\xe2n dou\u0103 \xeentreb\u0103ri evidente.\\n\\n**\xcentrebare num\u0103rul 1:** De ce intermediarii trebuie s\u0103 verifice tranzac\u021bii str\u0103ine?\\n\xcen primul r\xe2nd deoarece ei \xeensu\u0219i vor folosi mai u\u0219or LN. \xcen al doilea r\xe2nd, deoarece ei vor primi din toat\u0103 asta un comision foarte mic, dar totu\u0219i comision. \xcen acest moment, re\u021beaua este \xeentre\u021binut\u0103 \xeen mare parte de entuzia\u0219ti iar comisionul este aproape 0: 1 satoshi, sau 0.01 cent pentru fiecare intermediar.\\n\\n\\n\ud83d\udc4d Capacitatea canalelor - nu este o resurs\u0103 mai scump\u0103 dec\xe2t m\u0103rimea blocului. Deschiderea canelelor se face u\u0219or \u0219i necostisitor. De aceea comisioanele \xeen LN sunt cu mult mai mici dec\xe2t comisioanele din Blockchain.\\n\\n**\xcentrebarea num\u0103rul 2:** Cum e cu comisionul la deschiderea/\xeenchiderea canalului?\\n\\n\xcentradev\u0103r, acest comision poate fi uneori \u0219i zeci de dolari. \xcen acest fel, pl\u0103\u021bile vor fi mai profitabile dac\u0103 se vor deschide/\xeenchide canale mai pu\u021bine. Aceasta motiveaz\u0103 oamenii s\u0103 deschid\u0103 canale cu depozite mari, \u0219i s\u0103 foloseasc\u0103 canalele \xeen dou\u0103 direc\u021bii: nu doar pentru pl\u0103\u021bile care pleac\u0103 ci \u0219i pentru cele care vin. De exemplu: eu deschid un canal, fac o depunere de 1000$, \u0219i folosesc canalul dat doar pentru pl\u0103\u021bile de ie\u0219ire. Valoarea canalului va fi de 1000 dolari, din care undeva 20 de doloari se vor pl\u0103ti pentru deschiderea/\xeenchiderea canalului. Adic\u0103, comisia total\u0103 va fi de 2%. Un pic mai bine dec\xe2t cum e la Visa \u0219i Mastercard, dar evident mai mult dec\xe2t a\u0219 fi dorit. Situa\u021bia se schimb\u0103 drastic c\xe2nd eu \xeencep s\u0103 folosesc Lightning la maxim: f\u0103c\xe2nd depozite mai mari \u0219i primind bani prin intermediul canalelor, ci nu doar cheltuindu-i. Atunci, depinz\xe2nd de propor\u021bia intrare/ie\u0219ire a banilor, canalul poate fi deschis la infinit \u0219i comisioanele vor tinde spre zero.\\n\\n### 4.4. Critici\\nPe internet se poate g\u0103si o mul\u021bime de critici legate de solu\u021bia    layer-ului 2 \u0219i de Lighting Network \xeen general. Careva puncte \xeentradev\u0103r merit\u0103 aten\u021bie, multe - trebuie deja uitate. C\xe2teva exemple:\\n\\n1. **Folosirea LN va duce la centralizare: utilizatorii vor fi motiva\u021bi s\u0103 se conecteze la hub-uri mari iar aceste hub-uri vor controla tot traficul.**\\n\\nUn asemenea risc exist\u0103, dar acesta este foarte mic. \xcen primul r\xe2nd, e foarte economic \u0219i foarte simplu de realizat un nou nod care va respinge hub-urile mari. \xcen al doilea r\xe2nd, algoritmii de rutare urm\u0103resc balansarea traficului. \xcen al treilea r\xe2nd, la acest moment, asemenea problem\u0103 nu exist\u0103.\\n\\n2. **Capacitatea mic\u0103 a canaleleor va face ca LN s\u0103 fie suprasolicit\u0103, comisioanele vor cre\u0219te \u0219i cel mai probabil situa\u021bia va fi la fel, ca \u0219i \xeen Blockchainul de baza.**\\n\\n\xcenc\u0103 o dat\u0103, \xeendat\u0103 ce a\u0219a ceva se va \xeent\xe2mpla, persoanele vor fi motivate s\u0103 deschid\u0103 noduri personale. \xcen compara\u021bie cu m\u0103rimea blocului, num\u0103rul de noduri, este practic nelimitat\u0103.\\n\\n3. **O rutare efectiv\u0103 la un num\u0103r mare de noduri peer-to-peer este imposibil\u0103. Mai ales \u021bin\xe2nd cont de dificultatea deschiderii a noi canale.**\\n\\nP\xe2n\u0103 la o asemenea problem\u0103 este foarte \u0219i foarte departe iar cercet\u0103rile \xeen acest domeniu \xeen mod activ au loc chiar \xeen acest moment. Cu siguran\u021b\u0103 se vor lua ceva m\u0103suri.\\n\\n4. **Canele sunt nevoie mereu s\u0103 fie deschise \u0219i \xeenchise, comisioanele folosite pentru a\u0219a ceva vor fi mari iar folosirea LN nu se va merita.** \\n\\nDefapt, problema dat\u0103 este deja din trecut, pe care, nu \xeen\u021beleg de ce, \xeenc\u0103 o discut\u0103. Ceva timp \xeen urm\u0103, versiunile canalelor de plat\u0103 \xeentradev\u0103r, erau doar \xeentr-o singur\u0103 direc\u021bie, iar canalul putea s\u0103 existe doar o perioad\u0103 scurt\u0103 de timp. Acum aceste probleme sunt rezolvate.\\n\\n5. **Pentru folosirea LN este nevoie s\u0103 fii online.**\\n\\n\xcen compara\u021bie cu versiunile anterioare ale LN, utilizatorul nu este nevoit s\u0103 se afle tot timpul online: alte noduri din re\u021bea  vor verifica c\u0103 doi de\u021bin\u0103tori ale canalului de plat\u0103 nu \xeencearc\u0103 s\u0103 se mint\u0103 unul pe altul. \xcen mod cert, trebuie s\u0103 fii online doar pentru trimiterea \u0219i primirea pl\u0103\u021bilor, care f\u0103r\u0103 nici o \xeendoial\u0103 este un neajuns, dar de aceast\u0103 dat\u0103, mult mai neimportant.\\n\\n6. **LN - aceasta nu este sigur.**\\nPl\u0103\u021bile LN sunt un pic mai periculoase dec\xe2t pl\u0103\u021bile f\u0103cute direct \xeen Blockchain. Dar, doar \xeentrun singur context: un atac cu succes de 51% asupra Blockchain-ului Bitcoin. Riscul dat este unul catastrofic de mic.\\n\\n\\n## 5. LN ast\u0103zi\\n\\nLucrul cel mai important pe care trebuie s\u0103-l cunoa\u0219te\u021bi: \\n**Lighthing** deja se folose\u0219te \u0219i func\u021bioneaz\u0103 \xeen realiate.\\n\\nMai mult de o mie de noduri \xeen re\u021beaua de testare bitcoin \u0219i mai mult de 200 de noduri(num\u0103rul cre\u0219te \xeen fiecare zi) \xeen re\u021beaua de baz\u0103 bitcoin(mainnet) deja verific\u0103 pl\u0103\u021bi.\\n\\n<blockquote class=\\"twitter-tweet\\" data-lang=\\"en\\"><p lang=\\"en\\" dir=\\"ltr\\">Anyone want to help bug test new <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/Blockstream?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">@Blockstream</a> <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/LightningNetwork?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">#LightningNetwork</a> store? The Github repos should make it easy enough for even <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/coinbase?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">@coinbase</a> &amp; <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/BitPay?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">@BitPay</a> to integrate with the second layer. Cypherpunks do not whine they write code. Right <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/adam3us?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">@adam3us</a>? <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/MYOTHERNODEISASATELLITE?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">#MYOTHERNODEISASATELLITE</a> <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/DONTTRUSTVERIFY?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">#DONTTRUSTVERIFY</a> <a href=\\"https://t.co/Il3YBvirYo\\">pic.twitter.com/Il3YBvirYo</a></p>&mdash; Trace Mayer (@TraceMayer) <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/TraceMayer/status/953430172019101696?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\\">January 17, 2018</a></blockquote> <script async src=\\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\\" charset=\\"utf-8\\"><\/script> \\n\\n\\nCe \u021bine de softuri - exist\u0103 trei implement\u0103ri de baz\u0103, lnt de la Lightning Labs, c-lightning de la Blockstream, eclair de la ACINQ.\\n\\nAceste echipe, nu doar de un an lucreaz\u0103 \xeempreun\u0103, pentru a dezvolta un standard comun de interac\u021biune a nodurilor: Lighthing Network Specifications(BOLTs). \u0218i uite c\u0103 chiar la sf\xe2r\u0219itul anului 2017, au testat protocolul de pl\u0103\u021bi, \xeempreun\u0103, \u0219i toate cele trei implement\u0103ri au fost cu succes. \\n\\nS\u0103 achi\u021bi cu bitcoini reali folosind LN, se poate doar la c\xe2teva magazine online. Dar, asta e doar cu c\xe2teva magazine mai multe dec\xe2t acum o lun\u0103, iar acesta deja este succes. \\n\\nDesigur, momentul general de transfer de la on-chain bitcoin la pl\u0103\u021bi off-chain este \xeenc\u0103 foarte departe. O munc\u0103 imens\u0103 urmeaz\u0103 s\u0103 o fac\u0103 dezvoltatorii de portofele virtuale, nodurile de plat\u0103, bursele, magazinele-online, \u0219i, nu \xeen ultimul r\xe2nd - utilizatorii. Cel mai interesant \xeen aceast\u0103 istorie este c\u0103 tranzac\u021bii mult mai rapide, anonime \u0219i gratis - sunt doar \xeenceputul! Urmeaz\u0103 o mai mult\u0103 anonimitate, swap-uri atomice, schimburi distribuite \u0219i mult, mult mai mult.\\n\\nViitorul arat\u0103 interesant!"},{"id":"/2018/01/11/macbook-upgrade-first-impresions","metadata":{"permalink":"/2018/01/11/macbook-upgrade-first-impresions","source":"@site/blog/2018-01-11-macbook-upgrade-first-impresions.md","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Macbook Upgrade. First Impressions","description":"First of all, I will tell you how I started using the Apple ecosystem.","date":"2018-01-11T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 11, 2018","tags":[],"readingTime":4.16,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Alexandru Ilies"}],"frontMatter":{"layout":"post","title":"\ud83d\ude80 Macbook Upgrade. First Impressions","author":"Alexandru Ilies"},"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83d\ude80 Despre Lightning Network","permalink":"/2018/01/29/despre-lightning-network"}},"content":"First of all, I will tell you how I started using the Apple ecosystem.\\n\\nBack in 2013, when I was in my second year at the university, I got involved in an iOS internship. It was the first time I had ever used a macOS system, which was running on a Mac mini computer. I enjoyed using the system, and a few days after the internship started, I installed a Hackintosh version of Mavericks on my Asus notebook in order to use it at home and practice iOS development. The Hackintosh system ran pretty well, but the only problem I had was with the WiFi adapter, which was not supported, and I had to use a LAN cable every time. However, I was happy that I could learn iOS development without paying for an expensive Mac computer.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nAfter the internship, I continued to use the Hackintosh system to work on some projects at the university. As a result, my experience and motivation to buy an Apple computer grew.\\n## My old MacBook \\n-----\\nAbout 3 years later, in December 2016, I bought my first Apple computer. It was a MacBook Pro from 2015 with a 13-inch display, i7 3.1 GHz CPU, 16 GB of RAM, and 256 GB of SSD space. To be honest, it was my second computer, which I bought just a few days later than the first one. You can read why I made this decision on [Quora](https://www.quora.com/Should-a-computer-science-student-get-a-13-or-15-inch-MacBook-Pro/answer/Alexandru-Ilie%C8%99?srid=SKYq).\\n\\nThis MacBook Pro was and still is a powerful computer, and it helped me to be more organized, efficient, and even happier in what I do.\\n## My new MacBook\\n----- \\nI didn\'t have any essential reasons to upgrade my computer. It wasn\'t a burning desire, but then I created and advertised it on a local selling site two weeks ago. After that, someone wanted to buy it, and I wasn\'t prepared to part with it. I thought about keeping my old computer, but then I found an interesting advertisement. It wasn\'t a selling one, but a \\"changing\\" advertisement. The person who owned a MacBook Pro 2016 with touch bar, 13\\" display, 16 Gb of RAM, i7 3.3, and 512 Gb of SSD space wished to change it with the same configuration of MacBook Pro with a 15\\" display. I contacted him, and after a negotiation, he agreed to sell the computer to me. To be honest, it wasn\'t the best deal, and for a few hundred dollars more, I could have bought a more powerful MacBook Pro with a quad-core processor and a discrete GPU, but that\'s not what I wanted. The 13\\" display fit perfectly with my requirements. Even though the performance is lower than its 15\\" brother, it\'s still sufficient for my needs since I don\'t do any rendering or video gaming.\\n\\n## What makes the difference\\n-----\\nI\'ve seen many opinions regarding the new MacBook Pro computers. Some people are saying that the upgrade is not worth it if you already own a 2015 model. Others are saying that it is worth it, but there are some things they hate, like the touch bar, keyboard, performance (because of 32 GB of RAM), and so on. Here are my two cents on the differences I\'m experiencing right now.\\n\\nI\'ve owned the described new computer for 4 days, and I did not expect to experience so many changes, but I am.\\n\\nSo, here are the things I love:\\n\\n### The performance\\nThe performance is really great. I should do some more PC experiments, but I saw the improvements when I built/rebuilt iOS applications. It takes considerably less time.\\n### The keyboard\\nI really love the new keyboard. It is so lovely to touch it and to write. I am more accurate doing this( using [QWERTY](http://www.typingstudy.com/lesson/1/part/1) writing style, without looking at the keyboard)\\n### The cooling system\\n\\nWith a new version of the processor and two cooling fans, plus some other improvements - the experience is awesome. While building iOS apps or other way stressing CPU tasks, the old computer\'s fan had up to 7000 rpm/minute. On a low-performance tasks, it was at 1500/2000 rpm/minute. \\n    \\nOn the new computer, the maximum rotation rate I registered was 2000 rpm/minute and you can\'t even hear them. The most interesting part, at low-performance tasks, it shows 0 rpm/minutes.\\n    \\n![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/fgb567y720jijft/Screen%20Shot%202018-01-14%20at%2014.53.11.png?raw=1)\\n    \\nI really enjoy this improvement. I may say I have some allergy on fan sound because I hate it so much( I had some experience in the past with some desktop computer, but this is another story).\\n\\n### The battery\\nBecause of the cooling system, I think(of course and other stuff) the battery lasts for about - 7 hours. It is really enough for an entire workday.\\n    \\n### Touch bar\\nHere is really simple. I do not hate or love it. On the other hand, I find the Touch ID very useful. \\n    \\n## Conclusion\\n-----\\nI think, generally, the upgrade is worth it. Especially for me, when thinking again about the cooling system."}]}')}}]);